title: lentil barley soup
directions: Add everything except carrots.
Cook to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add carrots and simmer for 15 minutes or until tender.
Top with one cup of Swiss cheese and serve.

title: marinated sliced tomatoes
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes (about 5 slices each).
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over tomatoes.
Chill, covered, for at least one hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: glorified hamburg
directions: Put in 2-quart casserole.
Add more cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice squash, after washing, and cook 25 minutes.
Use very little water.
Add, while hot, the cream cheese; let cool.
Add American cheese.
Place in casserole.
Add grated Cheddar cheese, sprinkled over top, then bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Will serve 10 people.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine the cake and pudding mixes, then add the eggs, oil and 7-Up.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Makes a 3 layer cake.
Frost with vanilla frosting,
or frosting recipe for 7-Up cake.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except milk and margarine.
Cook over medium heat for 40 minutes, covered.
Add milk and margarine; simmer for 30 minutes.
For cream of potato soup, mash 1/2 of cooked potatoes and add finely shredded Cheddar cheese.
May reduce water and use milk instead of evaporated milk.

title: creamy chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken and onion in margarine.
Add tomatoes, peppers, milk and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover. Simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
Uncover. Cook 20 minutes.

title: banana bread(diabetic recipe)
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl and mix well.
Spray pan well with Pam.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter and cheese together; add flour, salt and pepper. Mix well. Add Rice Krispies. Drop spoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes. These store well for later use. Makes 6 dozen.

title: great peach cobbler
directions: Put Bisquick in bowl.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and butter.
Mix all and sprinkle over peaches that have been placed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Drizzle glaze made from powdered sugar and water over cobbler while still hot.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of glaze and strawberries. Refrigerate.

title: lightning cake
directions: To melted butter and lard, add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add all to the dry ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° to 375° about 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla extract until smooth.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in cupcake paper round side down.
Fill with 1 tablespoon of filling, about 3/4 full.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 24 tarts.

title: astoria hotel cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and food coloring.
Add sifted flour, salt and cocoa alternately with buttermilk.
Mix in flavor.
Stir in vinegar and soda without beating.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream the fat.
Add the brown sugar gradually, then the well-beaten eggs, milk and flour (mixed and sifted with the soda). Stir in the melted chocolate, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: beef chow mein
directions: Cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice with chow mein noodles and soy sauce.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix carrots, pepper and onion.
Combine other ingredients and add to vegetables.
Marinate at least 24 hours.
Serve cold from refrigerator.
These will last from 1 to 2 weeks or longer.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Combine sesame seed, paprika and salt.
Dip chicken in milk; roll in crumbs.
Pour butter or margarine in baking dish.
Place chicken in pan; turn once.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In small glass measure, combine milk with vanilla and almond extract and set aside.
In a large bowl of electric mixer at high speed, cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Alternately add 1/4 flour with 1/3 milk mixture.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack 15 minutes.
Serve plain or sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: incredible edible crabmeat
directions: Place cream cheese in the middle of serving dish.
Combine all ingredients except crabmeat in a small bowl and blend well.
Pour over the cream cheese.
Pile the crabmeat on top of the sauce and season with the meat seasoning.
Serve with your favorite crackers.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cherry almond preserves
directions: In a large kettle, bring the cherries and water to a boil. Boil for 15 minutes. Add sugar and bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 4 minutes. Stir in pectin. Return to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in extract.
Skim off foam.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 15 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Yields 11 half pints.

title: crispy french onion rings
directions: Mix flour, salt, milk, oil and egg white; beat until smooth. Add enough water to make a medium thin batter (about 6 tablespoons).
Peel 2 to 3 large onions; slice about 1/4 inch thick and separate into rings.
Dip rings into batter and drop in hot oil.
This makes a lot of onion rings.

title: popovers
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tin and bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 large or 24 small muffins.
Kids love these.

title: cabbage melange
directions: In a large heavy skillet, heat the oil over medium heat.
Add the remaining ingredients except the soy sauce.
Stir the mixture until the vegetables are lightly coated with the oil.
Cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle the mixture with soy sauce. Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: apricot gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water, then add rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart Pyrex and set until firm.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and broth, then mix cornstarch and water and add to mixture.
Cook sauce until thickened.
Add pineapple chunks to sauce.
Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover.
Add green pepper strips and keep basting with sauce.
Bake; uncover for additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet (cast-iron works best) and saute onion, garlic, pepper and rice.
Add seasonings and brown the rice.
Then add the tomato sauce and 1 can water.
Stir, cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli according to package directions in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grit bread
directions: Cook 1 c. grits & 4 cups water until thick.
Add 1 stick butter, 4 oz. grated sharp cheddar cheese, 1 roll Kraft garlic cheese and cook until melted.
Add 3 beaten eggs. Stir until mixed.
Put into a 1 1/2-2 qt. casserole and top with sharp cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until set in middle.

title: viennese raspberry squares
directions: Mix the butter and about half the flour.
Add the sugar and egg yolks and beat on medium speed until combined, scraping sides of bowl.
Stir in remaining flour.
Press into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add cream of tartar to the egg whites.
Beat on medium speed until soft peaks form.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in the chopped nuts.
Spreads preserves over the top of the hot baked crust.
Spread meringue over the top of the preserves.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut out centers of tomatoes.
Turn tomatoes upside down on paper towel to drain.
Put good tomato centers in bowl with celery, salt, pepper, onions and enough bread to soak up moisture.
Fill drained tomatoes.
Sprinkle sugar on shell when filled if baking (if not, sprinkle in stuffing) and butter on top.
Put tomatoes on pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients
together.	Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at
for about 45 minutes or until brown. Insert a toothpick.	If
it	comes out clean, it is done.
Let cool before cutting.

title: yum yum rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 20 minutes; scald milk and pour over sugar, butter and salt.
Let cool to lukewarm, then add yeast.
Beat eggs and add.
Beat in flour.
Place in bowl; brush top with melted fat and let rise until double in bulk about 1 hour.
Make in buns; bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: molded strawberry delight
directions: In large bowl stir gelatin and water until gelatin is dissolved; set aside 1 cup.
To remaining gelatin add 3/4 cup cold water; chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in strawberries; pour into 4-cup gelatin mold or bowl.
Chill until almost set, about 1 1/2 hours.
In small bowl stir reserved gelatin, yogurt, honey and almond extract; pour over strawberry-gelatin mixture.
Chill until set, about 2 to 3 hours. Unmold onto serving platter, garnish.

title: easy lasagna ever
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to beef and mix thoroughly.
Spread a thin layer of sauce mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top noodles with half of remaining sauce mixture followed by half of cheese, then remaining noodles.
Top noodles with remaining sauce mixture and all but 1/4 cup remaining cheese.
Pour boiling water right into the edge of the pan to within 1/2-inch of the top.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 40 minutes. Uncover and bake for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on during last 10 minutes of baking time.
Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing.
Serves 12.

title: chicken salad
directions: Put chicken in food processor or cube very small. Add all the ingredients. Chill. Serve on bed of leaf lettuce. Great on croissants.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Oil a large cookie sheet and line with wax paper.
Mix together the sugar, eggs and pumpkin. Add the flour, cinnamon and dash of salt.
Pour mixture on the cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes at 375°. Will be a thin layer.
When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Lay a tea towel over warm cake and flip over carefully. Remove wax paper. Roll cake up with towel. Let rest for 1 hour.
Unroll and spread with filling.

title: lou's hamburgers
directions: Mix altogether and wet hands.
Make patties.
Cook on grill until done or as desired.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in bottom of pie crust.
Mix 1 cup of milk with instant pudding until smooth.
Let set 3 minutes.
Stir spices in pumpkin.
Fold in instant pudding.
Spread over cheese in pie crust.
Chill for 2 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nutmeg and sliced toasted almonds.

title: grandma olson's german chocolate cake(very easy cake to make plus serves a large crowd)
directions: Put all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Boil 1 cup water; add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Add to mixture, beating with a spoon until smooth.
Mixture will be very thin.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes; check for doneness with a toothpick.

title: penne st. martin
directions: Heat olive oil and butter with garlic.
Cook until garlic is golden, then remove pieces and discard.
Add tomatoes to oil; simmer 4 minutes.
Add mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Add all spices and peas; cook until peas are tender.
Heat water to boil in large pot.
Cook pasta al dente.
While pasta is cooking, stir cream into sauce.
Cook until heated through.
Pour hot sauce over penne.
Add half Parmesan cheese and toss.
(Pass remaining Parmesan cheese at the table.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: glazed chicken(from mjb rice)
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Mix flour, paprika and garlic. Add chicken and toss to coat. Stir-fry chicken in hot oil until lightly browned. Add broth; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and next 5 ingredients. Blend mixture into ingredients in pan, stirring until sauce boils. Add pea pods. Cover and cook until tender-crisp.
Serve over rice.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, combine the sauces.
After browning the meat, add some of the sauce to the meat. Mix well. Add Ricotta to meat mixture and mix well.
Spray lasagna pan with nonstick spray and put a little sauce in the bottom.

Now start layering meat and cheeses until everything is gone, finishing with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until hot all the way through. Serve with hot garlic bread or fresh Italian bread.

title: po-boy mix
directions: Place roast in large covered roasting pan.
Add 6 to 8 cups water (more if needed),
Lipton soup mix, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until meat is fork-tender.
Remove meat from broth and allow meat to cool overnight in refrigerator.
Slice meat thin across the grain.
Add onions, garlic, tomato sauce and Lea & Perrins to broth.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Place sliced meat back in broth and heat through.
Freezes well.
Happy cooking.

title: girdle buster
directions: Crumble cookies.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour margarine over mixture.
Spoon softened ice cream over layer.
Pour syrup and nuts over layer of ice cream.
Cover and freeze overnight. Next morning, spread Cool Whip over top and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: easy chocolate delight pie
directions: Heat all but 3 squares of chocolate with 1/4 cup milk in large microwavable bowl at High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted.
Or heat in heavy saucepan over very low heat. Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature until pie can be cut easily.
Melt remaining chocolate about 15 seconds; drizzle over pie.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix well and pat into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan the cake mix, melted butter and eggs.
Beat well and pour over cake mixture the cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Parboil whole zucchini; allow to cool.
Slice 1/4 to 1/2-inch thickness; allow water to drain on paper towels.
Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Layer ingredients in baking pan in following order:
1) sauce 2) zucchini slices 3) Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Go back to 1.
Top layer should be cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Last 15 minutes, bake, uncovered, to allow cheese to brown slightly.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip fresh vegetables in dip. Best if made day before.

title: brownies
directions: In double boiler, melt oleo and chocolate.
Cool slightly. Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Add flour and milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a 13 x 15-inch pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, corn syrup, 2/3 cup sugar, melted butter and brown sugar.
Beat the filling mixture until well combined. Stir in pecan halves.
Pour filling into the unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes or until a knife inserted between the center and edge comes out clean.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Toss all ingredients together, adding mayonnaise and sugar mixture just before serving, coating all ingredients well.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.
Serve on a croissant or lettuce leaf.
Makes 8 to 9 croissants.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Grate cheese; cut onions. Put sour cream, soup, chilies and onions in saucepan and heat. Drop tortillas in 1/2-inch oil for a few seconds. Put tablespoon of heated mixture in center of tortillas. Sprinkle small handful of cheese inside tortilla; roll and put seam side down in baking pan. Pour remainder of heated mixture over tortillas. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sea coast salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed. Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly. Chill. Add additional salad dressing before serving.

title: greek meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger with rice, yellow onion, parsley, dill and egg. Mix and mold into small meatballs.
Roll each in flour.
In a large frying pan, put tomato juice and water.
Bring to heavy simmer and add butter.
Gently drop meatballs into this sauce, cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: four chip fudge
directions: Line 13 X 9 X 2 inch pan with foil and grease with the 1 1/2 tsp. butter, set aside.
In a large heavy sauce pan, melt the remaining butter over low heat.
Add the next five ingredients. Cook and stir constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in butterscotch chips, marshmallow cream and extracts until well blended.
Stir in nuts if you like.

title: angel pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Slowly add both sugars, beating constantly.
Lightly butter 9 or 10-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Pour in meringue mixture.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from oven; cool.
If center of pie shell doesn't fall, push in.
When cooked, fill with sweetened whipped cream.
Top with grated chocolate. Decorate with strawberries or raspberries.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, vanilla, salt and sugar.
Form 1-inch balls.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate bits and paraffin.
Dip balls in liquid.
Place on wax paper.

title: jimmy's pico de gallo
directions: Chop tomatoes; discard seeds.
Add chopped onion and chopped peppers.
Discard seeds.
Mix and sprinkle with salt.
Chop about 1 cup of cilantro leaves (rinse to remove grit).
Add cilantro and mix.
Squeeze all lemon juice from 1 lemon over mixture. Refrigerate about 2 hours, then break out the chips or flat bread. Excellent on fajitas, hot dogs, omelets, crackers, burgers; get the picture!

title: homemade mincemeat
directions: Mix
all ingredients together in a large pot and simmer 1 hour.
Pack
hot into jars and process pints and quarts for 20 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: chocolate graham cracker(refrigerator pudding)
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together.
Remove from heat and beat white egg yolks one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites (stiffly beaten).
Pour 1/2 of mixture over a layer of 12 graham crackers on a 13 x 9 inch pan.
Repeat second layer.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
You may spread on top of dessert.

title: lomo saltado
directions: Chop steak into pieces.
Fry potatoes, steak, onion and tomato.
Add spices.
Serve over rice.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and eggs.
Pour in greased and floured cake pan.
Top with chips, sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheeses well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Layer cheeses on top.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together ingredients in order listed.
Drop by large tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cheese and beefaroni with biscuit
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients together and place in a	casserole dish.
Place biscuit on top and bake for at least 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry-eggnog shake
directions: Soften ice cream in a large chilled mixer bowl.
Add mashed berries; beat with electric mixer just to blend.
Stir in eggnog. Serve in tall chilled glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: peach torte
directions: Bake cake in 3 layers according to directions.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar, nutmeg and milk.
Mix with electric mixer until fluffy. Drain peaches; reserve juice.
Mash peaches (save a couple to decorate with).
Take drained mashed peaches and add 1 cup of icing mix.
Stir, then use to fill between layers.
Pour peach juice over each layer as you stack cake, then filling.
Top cake and sides with the plain icing and decorate with peaches. This cake can be done with pineapple instead of peaches.

title: john's favorite pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and stir with wooden spoon.
Add sifted flour and all other ingredients.
Cook on medium heat in an iron skillet until thickened.
Mix until smooth and pour into pie shell.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs. Peel and cool. Dice potatoes, eggs, celery, pepper, and onion. Mix all together and add salad dressing, pickle relish, sugar, mustard and salt and pepper. Chill until ready to serve. Serves 6.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, sugar and flour in heavy saucepan.
Stir in milk and eggs.
Cook on medium-high heat until comes to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in margarine and flavoring.
Remove from heat.
Allow to cool for 5 minutes.
Pour in pie shell.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.

title: christmas salad(yields 12 servings)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water in bowl.
Stir in 1 cup cold water.
Chill until partially set; combine cranberries with a small amount of water in blender container; process at medium speed for several seconds or until chopped.
Drain; combine with celery, apple, orange, pineapple, pecans and sugar in bowl and mix well.
Fold in gelatin.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch dish. Chill until set.
Serve as sauce with turkey or on lettuce leaves as salad.

title: baked angel's wings
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt with oleo as for pie crust.
Combine yolks, sour cream and flavoring.
Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 1/2 x 4-inch strips. Twist or knot.
Place on ungreased pans.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut or tear into pieces.
salt and pepper to taste.
Separate crescent rolls.
Roll chicken into individual crescent rolls and place in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Mix together cream of chicken soup and milk.
Pour over crescent rolls.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and cheddar rolls
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Tear along perforations.
Place 4 triangles on an ungreased baking sheet.
Spread lightly with mustard.
Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon cheese and 1 tablespoon cooked ham.
Starting at large end, roll dough toward point.
Fold ends in slightly to form "rolls."
Bake in a 375° oven for 11 to 13 minutes, or until golden.
Serves 4.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Cook broccoli until almost done.
Arrange broccoli in baking dish. Cover with chicken. Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup together.
Pour it over the broccoli and chicken.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter.
Cover casserole mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Preparation time:
15 to 20 minutes.

title: double-deck brownies
directions: Melt shortening; add sugar and eggs and mix well.
Mix flour and baking powder and add to first mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla. Divide in half and add chocolate to one half.
Spread chocolate mixture in 8-inch square greased pan.
Spread remaining half on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coca-cola fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken and place in skillet.
Mix Coke and ketchup together.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat to simmer.
Let simmer until chicken is tender.

title: apple muffins
directions: Measure and mix dry ingredients, flour, soda, salt and all spice, and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg and mix well.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk.
Mix until blended.
Fold in apples.
Spray muffin tins with Pam. Makes 12 small muffins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: mary's orange carrots
directions: Simmer sugar, margarine and orange juice for 15 minutes or until thickened.
Pour over carrots and oranges in casserole. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Heat until bubbly and carrots are candied. (May be mixed the day before and refrigerated overnight.)

title: momma's raspberry velvet pie
directions: Drain berries; reserve syrup.
Add enough water to make 1 cup. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows; stir until partly dissolved.
Add juice.
Chill until partly set.
Beat mixture.
Add berries and fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crusts.
Top before serving with more whipped cream.

title: cherry cake dessert
directions: Mix together pie filling and pineapple (do not drain) in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 box white cake mix over top.
Dot one stick of butter on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip to eat.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Fry ground beef in 1/4 inch of oil.
Cube green pepper, onion and celery. Put in skillet with ground beef.
Simmer until tender. Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain. Pour in tomato sauce, then add ground beef mixture to macaroni.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, milk, eggs, chips and nuts in a big bowl.

Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes. Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until cake springs back when lightly touched. Do not overbake.
Cool 15 minutes in pan. Remove from pan. Finish cooling on rack.
Ice with chocolate icing.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain and squeeze to remove excess moisture.
Combine spinach and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape mixture into 3/4-inch balls; place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken well in oil.
Remove and drain.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: corn for freezer
directions: Boil gently together for 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Chill in pan with ice around it and stir part time while cooling.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light and add to sugar.
Blend mashed bananas and lemon juice to creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan (9 x 5-inches) in moderate oven (325°) for about one hour.
This recipe may be doubled.
Bake in 2 loaf pans.

title: wheat thins
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix with fingers.
Add enough cold water to stick together.
Knead.
Roll thin and cut in squares.
Prick each with fork.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until brown and crisp.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cake rack.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch).
On wax paper thoroughly stir together the flour baking soda, salt and spices.
In a large mixing bowl beat together until smooth the sugar, corn oil, eggs and vanilla.
Slowly beat in the flour mixture; stir in apples and nuts.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean, 1 1/4 hours.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes, then turn out on pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix peas, eggs, mayo, relish, salt and pepper well.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: fig bars
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Spread over greased pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: london broil marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer on stove for a minimum of one hour.

title: scallop and squid stir-fry
directions: Chop all vegetables (slice mushrooms).
Clean squid (very important).
Stir-fry squid in 1 tablespoon olive oil for 40 minutes.
Add sesame oil.
Add broccoli and peppers.
After 8 to 11 minutes, add the rest of the vegetables; stir-fry for 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Add spices/soy sauce while stirring occasionally. Add scallops; stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Begin to boil water for pasta when cooking broccoli and peppers.
Add pasta to water in time to finish with scallops.
Serve stir-fry over fettucine.

title: chocolate frosting 3
directions: Cook over low heat until margarine is melted and smooth.
Add powdered sugar; take off heat and stir until desired consistency. Pour over cake.
Add pecans (optional).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender. When they have cooled, debone the chicken. Place 1/2 package of dressing in bottom of casserole dish. Melt margarine; pour over dressing mix. Place chicken in casserole dish. Blend sour cream and soup together; spread over chicken.
Put remaining dressing over sour cream mixture.
Pour 2 cups broth over casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, reserving some stuffing crumbs for topping.
Bake in casserole dish at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup(or cream of celery

title: english toffee
directions: Place sugar, butter or margarine and water in large, heavy pan. Cook for 10 minutes on very high flame until mixture turns golden brown, stirring constantly.
Pour on lightly buttered cookie sheet and quickly spread Hershey bars over hot base.
Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: brazilian black beans
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Salt and pepper roast.
Brown in oven for 30 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Add beans to roaster with enough water to cover beans.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake for approximately 2 hours, adding onion, more water and salt and pepper after first hour.
Beans become soft in a soup like broth.
Slice roast and serve beans over hot rice. Serves 6.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make yellow cake mix by directions on box into sheet cake. Punch holes in cake while hot.
Pour cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk over cake while hot.
Cool and put Cool Whip and frozen coconut on top.

title: ham and egg breakfast souffle
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon grease.
Mix together cornmeal, cheese, salt and pepper.
In a skillet, heat 1 tablespoon bacon grease with half of cooking oil. Coat tomato slices well with cornmeal mixture.
When grease is sizzling hot, cook tomatoes on both sides until crisp and lightly brown.
Repeat with remaining.
Drain on paper towel.
Transfer fried tomatoes to a large plate; sprinkle with crumbled bacon. Serve hot.

title: vegetable aspic
directions: In saucepan, heat 2 cups V-8 juice.
Add lemon jello and stir until dissolved (you may add 1 package dissolved in 1/4 cup hot water for a firmer set).
Add remaining V-8 juice, vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put crushed wafers.
Add butter until thoroughly mixed.
Spread on bottom and sides of pan.

title: thanksgiving dressing
directions: Put day old bread slices on cake pans in oven at 250° until slices are browned.
After cooled, soak browned slices a few seconds in water.
Squeeze out water well and gently.
Put bread in large bowl.
Brown chopped celery, onion, and butter together. Add this to bread.
Next, fold in cut up chicken (cooked). Lastly, add rest of ingredients.
Stir gently.
Stuff turkey and put rest of dressing in a 10 x 7 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
All stuffing ingredients are already cooked except eggs, so this doesn't need to be overbaked.

title: italian tomato soup
directions: Saute celery and onion until soft, but not brown.
Add soup, broth, tomatoes and seasoning; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini in cream
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 6 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish. Peel potatoes.
Cut lengthwise into one-sixteenth inch thick slices.
Place in a large bowl.
Cover with cold water; soak 5 minutes.
Drain, rinse and pat dry.
Using an electric mixer, beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour 1 cup into prepared dish. Top with 3 to 4 layers of potatoes, arranged in crisscross pattern. Cover with 1 cup of cream mixture.
Continue layering, ending with cream.
Press potatoes down to submerge.
Cover with foil.
Bake until knife easily pierces center, about 2 hours.
Remove foil and continue baking until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Run knife around edge of dish.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: catfish gumbo
directions: Chop pepper, onions, celery and garlic; saute in hot oil in Dutch oven until tender.
Stir in broth and next 6 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cut catfish into 1-inch pieces; add to gumbo.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in okra; cook an additional 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice.
Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: almond date squares
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together well.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Set aside. Boil dates in water for 5 minutes. If mixture is too dry, add a little more water.
Spread carefully over bottom layer.
Beat egg whites until frothy and turning white.
Add brown sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Spread over dates.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Cover to store.
Cut with clean knife.

title: nutty salmon patties
directions: Combine salmon with its liquid, crackers and Grape-Nuts cereal.
Mix well. Add egg, milk and onion. Stir until well blended.
Make into small patties. Fry in melted butter (I use Pam) in a skillet. Brown on both sides. Serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: far east celery
directions: Parboil celery in small amount of water for 8 minutes.
Drain. Add soup, pimentos, milk, chestnuts and cheese. Put into a greased casserole.
Toss crumbs with almonds in melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugar, vanilla and pudding mix in large bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: chicken-mushroom bake
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Shake chicken in flour mixture.
Melt butter in skillet.
Brown chicken.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, sour cream and mushrooms. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until tender. Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes, put in casserole dish, then mix up the soup like you would for soup (with milk or water).
Pour over potatoes. Wash off the pork chops and place them on top of the potatoes. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serves 5 people.

title: parsley soup
directions: Combine and bring to a boil potatoes, onion, butter, curry powder, Worcestershire and water.
Simmer until potatoes and onions are tender.
Combine parsley and chicken stock in blender and blend until smooth; add to potato and onion mixture.
Combine milk, heavy cream and pepper and add to rest of ingredients.
Heat and serve or chill and serve cold.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients 2-5 with bread crumbs.	Fold in ground beef and form into two loaves. Place in lined roaster uncovered.

title: company olives
directions: Drain liquid from jar of olives into saucepan.
Add garlic and pepper; simmer 5 minutes.
Add vinegar, dill and red pepper flakes.
Pour over olives (still in jar) and shake well.
Let stand in sealed jar in refrigerator at least 4 days.
The longer, the better.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Blend together and pour into ice cream maker.

title: underwood holiday bells
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat together cream cheese, deviled ham, Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper until smooth.
Stir in green and red peppers.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with crackers and vegetables.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger with garlic powder; shape into small balls. Pan-fry until well cooked; drain.
Mix chili sauce and jelly.
Add meatballs; heat mixture.
Serve warm in chafing dish with toothpicks neatly.
Yield:
12 servings as cocktail appetizer.

title: angel food ice cream cake
directions: Tear cake into three sections and place each section in a bowl. Pour one flavor of Jell-o (dry mix) over each section. Mix well. In a tube pan or other deep dish, layer as follows: orange cake mixture, drained mandarin oranges, ice cream. Raspberry cake mixture, blueberries, ice cream. Strawberry cake mixture, ice cream, drained strawberries. Place in freezer until ready to serve. Let sit out for about 5 minutes before serving.

title: honey dijon chicken nuggets
directions: Combine apricot spread, mustard, honey, pepper and garlic powder in a medium bowl and stir well.
Measure 1 cup apricot mixture and set aside.
Dip chicken pieces in remaining apricot mixture.
Dredge in crushed pretzels.
Place on 2 large baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well; if not creamy enough, I add a bit of half and half or milk.
Heat at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; remove and drain fat.
In saucepan, heat soup (do not add milk or water), stirring until smooth.
Add tomatoes and sausage.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Great on taco chips.

title: beef triangles
directions: Add powdered soup mix to ground beef and fry until brown. Open crescent rolls and cut each triangle in half; flatten out and place on wax paper.
Take one spoonful of beef mixture and place in the triangle.
Fold ends of crescent roll up to cover meat and form a triangle.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until golden brown. Makes 32 appetizers.

title: midnight muncher
directions: For each sandwich, hard-fry an egg, fry 3 slices of bacon, slice tomato and add lettuce.
Toast your bread and add mayonnaise or butter.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan and bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven or 20 minutes in microwave. Top with ketchup when taken from oven.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Place butter in a 4-cup glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until butter is melted.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Cook on medium for 1 minute, beating every 15 seconds until thickened.
Remove from oven and beat with mixer until light and smooth.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in strawberries last. Bake in two 9 x 5-inch pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in small saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add cornflake crumbs.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Melt remaining margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add onion and cook only until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Remove from heat and add milk, gradually stirring until smooth. Return to medium heat and cook until bubbly and thickened, stirring constantly.

title: seafood mousse
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover sole with 3/4 cup boiling water and poach 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool and drain.
Put fish, cooked shellfish and egg whites in the bowl of a processor and process until smooth.
Turn into a large chilled bowl and add brandy and seasonings.
Stir to blend.
Add cream slowly, mixing thoroughly until well blended and thick.
Pour into a buttered ring mold; place it in a pan filled with a few inches of hot water and bake 35 minutes, or until top is firm.
Unmold and serve hot with sauce.

title: "melt in your mouth" pork chops
directions: Trim all fat from chops.
Place in casserole.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or 250° for 2 hours or until chops are tender. Sauce is very good over baked potatoes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add the rest of the ingredients and mix.
Add one can of Baker's poppy filling.
Add one cup chopped walnuts (optional).
Beat well on medium for 2 minutes.

title: windsor hotel fricassee chicken
directions: Clean and cut chicken at the joints.
Put in large kettle; add water to cover chicken completely.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add onion, celery and carrots; season to taste. Continue to simmer for about 2 hours.
Remove chicken and vegetables.
Strain stock; remove all fat and measure stock. There should be 2 to 3 cups.

title: heavenly layered fruit
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk and then blend in Cool Whip.
Set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch container, layer angel food cake, drained pineapple and Cool Whip mixture.
Other fruit can be used.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and both sugars until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well; add bananas, buttermilk and water with baking soda and mix well.
Slowly add flour and mix until well blended.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into 9 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes then remove from pan and place on cooling rack.
Store in refrigerator (this tastes better after it has been stored in refrigerator for 24 hours).
This bread freezes well.

title: funnel cake
directions: You will need a funnel.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 12-cup muffin pan.
Pour into muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown. Makes 12 muffins.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together with a spoon the cake mix, oil and pineapple. Beat the eggs together with a fork; add to first mixture and mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
After cake has cooled, frost.

title: delicious braunschweiger log
directions: Blend all together and shape into a log.
Mix another 8 ounces cream cheese, softened, with dry mustard, salt, pepper and onion powder to taste.
Beat with electric blender until it looks like whipped cream.
"Ice" the log and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.
Recipe will feed several.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and crushed pineapple well; stir in other ingredients and mix well.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk; set aside.
Mix cake mix, butter and remaining evaporated milk.
Place half the batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chips on top, then pour melted caramels over chips.
Sprinkle nuts on top of that.
Pat down.
Put rest of batter on top and spread as well as possible.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: poor man's meal
directions: Peel potatoes and cube.
Boil in 2 quarts of water until tender.
Drain potatoes.
Add milk and margarine and mash.
Set aside.
In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain. Spread ground meat evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Place green beans evenly over meat.
Spread mashed potatoes over beans. Sprinkle shredded cheese over potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fat-free carrot cake
directions: Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: In bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat oleo, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
At low speed beat in next 4 ingredients; shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: batter rolls
directions: Add yeast, sugar, salt, oil and egg to milk.
Add 2 cups flour and beat well.
Gradually stir in more flour until mix is stiff. Let rise until double in bulk.
Drop by spoonful into well-greased muffin tin.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: shrimp tempura
directions: Blend and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Heat 3-inches oil in deep pot or 2-inches if using frypan.
Test oil with drop of batter. When drop goes to bottom of pan and pops back up light brown, oil is hot enough.
Dip cleaned, shelled shrimp in batter and fry until done.

title: stir-fry collard greens
directions: Break off and discard stems of collard.
Wash leaves thoroughly.
Slice leaves into bite-size pieces by rolling several leaves together and cutting into 1/4-inch strips.
Blanch greens in boiling water for 30 minutes.
Drain well.
Melt drippings in a large skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in tomato and cook until just tender.
Add greens to onion mixture and stir until well coated.
Cook until tender.
Stir in a pinch of nutmeg.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags and brew for a few minutes. Combine all ingredients.
Put one ice cream scoop in tall glass. Fill with 7-Up or ginger ale. Makes pretzel container full.

title: durango drummettes
directions: In large skillet, combine water, soy sauce, sherry, brown sugar and green onions.
Add drummettes and stir to coat. Heat to boiling and lower heat. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Uncover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes more. Serve warm.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt bacon drippings in a 9-inch cast-iron skillet in the oven.
Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Whisk eggs into buttermilk; add to the corn meal mixture, stirring just until blended.
Pour hot drippings from skillet into batter; blend well.
Pour batter into hot skillet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until cornbread is golden brown.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lora's bran muffins
directions: Put ingredients into a bowl.
Just fold until mixed.
Put into muffin pan.
Makes about 8 muffins.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess grease.
Add the onions, Italian seasoning, salt and tomato paste and warm through.
Grease muffin tins and pat out biscuits and place in the tins.
Add 1/4 cup meat mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: aunt goldie's fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into saucepan. Add the sugar, flour and eggs. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture bubbles and thickens. Cool.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook Karo, butter, water and sugar to form soft ball stage. (When dropped in cold water, it will form a soft ball.)
Pour mixture over popcorn and mix.
Put butter on your hand and dip your hands in cold water.
Form popcorn into balls.
Food coloring may be added to cooked mixture to color for different seasons. Put balls on wax paper to cool.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large heavy saucepan. Gradually stir in lemon mixture.
Add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon rind.
Pour into shell.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Add 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar.
Beat in vanilla.
Spread meringue over hot filling.
Seal to edge of crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: pork cantonese
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet.
Drain mushrooms and pineapple chunks; combine and measure liquids.
Add enough water to measured liquid to make 2 cups.
Add to skillet; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Stir in molasses, soy sauce and vinegar.
Add mushrooms, pineapple chunks, green pepper and onion. Cook 15 minutes longer.
Blend cornstarch with small amount of water; stir into hot mixture.
Cook, stirring until slightly thickened.
Serve with hot cooked rice.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Add eggs and 1/2 flour; mix well.
Add other 1/2 of flour to fruit and nuts.
Mix well. Add batter to fruit and nut mixture and mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 12 minutes or until done.
Yields a large amount.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Put ingredients through sieve 3 times.
Store in airtight container.

title: whipped dream dressing for fruit salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise by hand until smooth.
Stir in preserves, lemon juice and curry powder.
Chill until about an hour before serving.
Stir in whipped cream and refrigerate until serving time.
Yield:
about 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream powdered sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly. Stir next 8 ingredients together in a saucepan.

Cook over medium heat stirring constantly. Bring to a boiling point and cook a few minutes. Sprinkle 2/3 of peanut butter mixture in bottom of baked pie shell. Pour custard over this. Beat egg whites and spread on custard and sprinkle remainder of peanut butter mixture over egg whites and brown in oven.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Boil potatoes until firm (not soft).
Cool, peel and shred on large part of grater.
Heat butter, cheese and sour cream until almost melted.
Add sour cream, salt, pepper and green onion to cheese mixture; fold into potatoes.
Put in 2-quart casserole; heat until just heated through.
Reheat in microwave about 3 minutes.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Pour crackers into a gallon Ziploc bag.
Mix oil, dressing and spices together in a bowl.
Stir well.
Pour mixture into the bag with the crackers.
Seal the bag and shake well.
Continue to shake once a day until all crackers are eaten.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Put pineapple and sugar in pan.
Boil 4 minutes.
Dissolve jello in water; mix with pineapple.
Refrigerate until set.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Add to jello.
Mix well.
Chill until set.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, stir well, chill overnight.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over it.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes in it while still warm.
Heat ice cream topping.
Pour over warm cake.
Let cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray pie plate with cooking spray. Flatten biscuits in pie plate to form a crust.
Spread olive oil on biscuits.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Spread tomatoes on biscuits.
Sprinkle seasonings on tomatoes.
Mix cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread on tomatoes.
Bake until biscuits cook and cheese bubbles.

title: bacon twists
directions: Wrap slice of bacon around each bread stick.
Roll in Parmesan cheese.
Place on microwave bacon cooker and cook 6 to 8 minutes. Will be very crisp.
Place paper towel over and under to absorb grease.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill 3 hours.
Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: green beans viennese
directions: Cook green beans according to the package directions and drain.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a saucepan (3-quart), combine the rice and water.

Simmer for 10 minutes; add milk and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 60 to 70 minutes or until rice is tender. Add sugar, salt and butter; mix well. Add cinnamon to taste. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: "fat boy" apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Arrange in pie shell.
Combine other ingredients and mix until crumbly; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 425° for first 15 minutes, then at 350° for another 45 minutes. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: cherry oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Mix at medium speed until well mixed.
Add oats, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until well mixed. Fold in nuts and raisins.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
On floured surface, roll each biscuit to 1/8-inch thick.
Arrange biscuits on bottom and sides of pie pan to form a crust.
Brown meat, onion, green pepper and celery.
Stir in tomatoes with their liquids, salt and oregano.
In a small bowl, beat eggs and milk and add meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook noodles (or can substitute spaghetti) according to package directions.
Pour boiling water over smoked franks and let stand 5 minutes.
Dry.
Slice (cutting on a diagonal is nice for this salad) in small slices.
Add peppers.
Mix dry Italian seasoning mix, vinegar, oil, sugar and a few onion flakes.
Pour over salad and mix together.

title: cheese pecan spread
directions: With a beater or spoon, combine cream cheese with steak sauce. Add pecans, garlic, Tabasco sauce and parsley.
Mix well; form in ball and roll the ball over more pecans.
Then wrap in plastic wrap and chill for several hours.

title: cream of tomato soup(freezer)
directions: Melt butter.
Saute garlic, celery and onions.
Add cored, cut-up tomatoes, stock and parsley.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Put all through food mill.
Return to pot and reheat.
Add salt and pepper.

title: chocolate (star cookie) filled snowballs
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add sifted flour and nuts; blend well.
Chill dough.
Remove foil from kisses.
Shape dough around kisses, until about 1 tablespoon dough for each ball.
Be sure to cover kisses completely in ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until set but not brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove carefully to wire racks.
While still warm, sprinkle top with confectioners sugar; cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Roll in sugar again before serving, if desired.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: peppered steak
directions: Cut beef in 1/8-inch thick strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef; toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.

title: birdie roquefort
directions: Brush chicken with melted butter and A.1.; combine sour cream with Roquefort, salt and paprika.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or 350° for 1 hour.

title: superb pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box with the following variations:
Use 2 more eggs than the directions call for and substitute pineapple juice for liquid.
Then add the can of drained, crushed pineapple to the cake batter and mix well.

title: oatmeal cake(edna jean alfson)
directions: Pour hot water over quick oatmeal and let stand for 20 minutes.
Sift the flour and add cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Washed and pat dry the chicken breasts.
Marinate with garlic powder, onion powder, cajun seasoning, and crushed red pepper flakes.
Add a bit of water and boil until chicken is tender. Let cool then cut into thin strips.
Set aside.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Combine egg, sour cream and cooking oil.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients, add liquid ingredients all at once.
Mix only until all ingredients are moist.
Fill well greased muffin cups 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: baked macaroni 'n cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in pepper, salt, mustard and flour.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Combine sauce, cheese and macaroni.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beef-broccoli-potato bake
directions: Brown ground beef.
Place potatoes in 2 1/2-quart pan.
Spread cooked ground beef over potatoes.
Spread frozen broccoli, broken apart, over beef.
Sprinkle powdered mixture from the potatoes over the broccoli.
Add butter to 1 cup of boiling water to melt.
Mix in sour cream and pour over casserole.
Pour remaining water over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with layer of beef, then cheese.
Combine both dressings; spread over cheese. Top with tomato slices; set aside.
Combine butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over tomato slices.
Microwave at 70% power for 12 to 14 minutes, or bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: In a very well buttered pan, alternate layers of potatoes, onion, cheese and salt and pepper until the pan is full.
Pour milk or cream over all; dot with butter.
Cover the pan with foil or lid.
Begin cooking over medium heat until cover is very hot to touch (about 20 minutes).
Reduce heat to low; cook about 25 minutes more.
Take cover off; cook additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; mash and drain.
Combine squash, onion, sour cream and soup.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and top with stuffing that has been mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda.
Let stand while other ingredients are mixed.
Add to date mixture and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° to 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Store while hot in airtight container.

title: potato salad
directions: As soon as the potatoes are cooked, drain.
Mix other ingredients except paprika and toss.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: hush puffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 8 muffin cups.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into muffin cups, 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: good dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine beaten egg, milk and oil and add to dry mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into at least 3 cups of liquid or into boiling water.
Cook 15 minutes or until done, part uncovered and part covered.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Make tea as desired.

title: dried beef snacks
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Spread on slices of dried beef. If slices of beef are small, use more than one slice to each roll.
Roll up tight like jelly roll.
Chill.
Cut in 1/2-inch pieces and pierce with toothpicks.

title: beefy rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 350 degrees for one hour.

title: mocha toddies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine coffee crystals and water.
Stir to dissolve crystals.
Add chocolate syrup, rum and vanilla.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
To serve, stir tablespoons Mocha Base into 3/4 cup milk in a mug.
Top with ice cream.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Beat eggs with salt and evaporated milk until well mixed.
Add fresh milk and sugar substitute.
Cook in top of double boiler until mixture is consistency of soft custard.
Add vanilla; mix well and remove from heat.
Toss sliced bananas with lemon juice and arrange in bottom of 9-inch graham cracker crust, reserving several slices for garnish.
Pour custard mix over the bananas. Arrange reserved slices on top and chill until well set.

title: christmas eve salad
directions: Place oranges, bananas, beets, pineapple and jicama in bowl. Mix reserved beet liquid and pineapple juice, then lemon juice, 2 tablespoons sugar and the salt; pour over fruit.
Let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Arrange fruit on shredded lettuce.
Garnish with lime, peanuts and pomegranate seed.
Mix anise seed and 1 tablespoon sugar; sprinkle over salad.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Mix the milk and extract.
Start adding powdered sugar 1 cup at a time.
Knead the last cup or so of sugar into the dough. Dough will be smooth and not too sticky.
Pinch off small pieces and pat into mint sized patties.
Place on cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Don't make patties too big as it makes them difficult to dip in the chocolate.
They shouldn't be any wider than a fork.
Let patties dry about an hour, the turn them over and dry on other side.
Dip in chocolate melted in a double boiler, one at a time.
Pull them out of the chocolate by scooping them up with a fork, tapping the extra chocolate back into the pan.
Turn the fork upside down and let the mint slide off onto another waxpaper lined cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: broiled parmesan potatoes
directions: Stir together butter or margarine, basil, paprika, garlic powder and pepper.
Place potato slices in a single layer on the unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Brush margarine mixture over both sides of potato slices.
Broil about 5-inches from heat for 8 to 9 minutes or until potatoes begin to brown.
Using a wide spatula, turn potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil for 4 to 6 minutes more or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: judy's dried apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and butter while apples are still warm. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth; add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla and coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in egg whites (beaten).
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes, or until tests done.

title: emerald isle mold
directions: Cream the cream cheese and blend with Jell-O.
Add water and juice.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: blueberry streusel muffins
directions: Combine first five ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.

title: quick upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 10 1/2 x 2-inch cast-iron skillet.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over butter.
Arrange 7 pineapple slices over brown sugar, reserving remaining slice for other uses.
Place a cherry in the center of each pineapple slice. Sprinkle with pecans.
Set aside.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt chips together in heavy saucepan.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheets or plates. Chill.
Makes 48 pieces of candy.

title: nutty sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until ingredients are set.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle peanuts and marshmallows over the top.
Place back in oven for 15 minutes.

title: deep fried pretzels
directions: Combine flour and plain salt in a bowl.
Cut in shortening. Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened and dough can be gathered into a ball.
Knead gently a few times.
Pinch off pieces of dough and shape into 1-inch balls. Roll each ball between hands to form a 10-inch rope. Form each rope into a pretzel shape.
Set on waxed paper.
Heat shortening to 365°.
Fry 3 pretzels at a time for 3 minutes or until brown. Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with coarse salt.

title: crisp chicken with herbs
directions: Mix
eggs,
1/2 teaspoon salt, milk and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper together.	In
another bowl mix other dry ingredients. Dip chicken
in
liquid
mixture
and then in the flour mix to coat. Fry
in
oil
in
14-inch
Dutch
oven, turning after 5 minutes. Cover
and	simmer 15 minutes, turning once.
Remove lid and cook for 15 minutes more.
Drain and serve.

title: breast rolls
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Pound to 1/4-inch thickness.
In a large glass bowl, mix together butter and pepper sauce for marinade.
Add chicken, turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 15 to 30 minutes.
Remove chicken, spoon 1 tablespoon cheese onto center of each chicken breast. Fold in sides of chicken around cheese. Fasten with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on Medium-high
(70%), 8 to 9 minutes.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with celery leaves.

title: chicken asparagus
directions: Place asparagus in casserole dish.
Brown chicken and layer over asparagus.
Mix soup, mayo and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Brown crackers in butter and sprinkle over soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: yummy fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Mix pudding in the juice off of the fruit with a whisk.
Add Tang and mix until well blended.
Put fruit into the pudding mixture; chill.
Add sliced bananas before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 c. nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix everything well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease 4 coffee cans.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and leave in cans until ready to serve.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in water until tender.
Add salt, milk, cheese, minced onion and celery soup.
Brown almonds in margarine.
Add to celery mixture and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: flan
directions: Sift brown sugar into bottoms of 8 custard cups or 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Beat slightly.
Add sugar and salt; blend in milk and vanilla.
Pour custard mixture over sugar in custard cups or baking dish.
Place cups or baking dish into shallow baking pan and fill halfway up baking dish with hot water.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise. Cover and refrigerate overnight, if possible.
tags: whole kernel white Shoe Peg corn

title: oneida corn soup
directions: Cook corn in water with bits of venison, wild edible greens like cowslip, ferns or milk weed and a handful of wild rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine well in large bowl.
Fashion into football shaped loaf in bottom of roaster pan.
Dust top with garlic powder.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours plus or minus.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook beef; then drain.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients, except celery seed, in a bowl. Add a small amount of vinegar to make a paste.
Add oil and vinegar alternately in small amounts.
Beat after each addition.
Add celery seeds.
Yields 3 cups.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Cook pork in water and salt and pepper to taste.
Remove pork when done and shred into small pieces.
Set aside.
Measure 1 cup broth and 1/4 cup onion into pot.
Add ketchup, mustard, parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Add pork.
Allow to simmer 15 to 20 minutes on low heat until onions are done.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box, then cream with Cool Whip and let get solid and ready to spread.

In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, put a layer of graham crackers (leave whole), 1 layer of cream mix, another layer of graham crackers, a layer of cream mix, another layer of graham crackers, a layer of chocolate icing. Refrigerate until used.

title: company's coming beef roast
directions: Line roast pan with foil.
Place nice size sirloin roast in pan.
Add soup mix and golden mushroom soup on top of roast.
Pour 1 cup of water (use soup can to measure and pour over roast). Cover roast with foil and roast pan cover.
Bake at 350° for approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
This roast makes its own gravy and when meat is tender, carrots and potatoes can be added and returned to oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot roast
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and put in oiled pan.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: kid size pizzas
directions: Let bread dough thaw until pliable.
Divide into 6 pieces. Pat each piece on floured board into circles 4 or 5 inches in diameter.
Put onto greased baking sheet.
Top with sauce and shredded cheese.
Top with toppings as desired.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: pinto beans and hamburger meat
directions: Cook beans until nearly done.
Brown hamburger meat and drain. Add all of the ingredients to the hamburger meat and saute a few minutes.
Add to the beans and finish cooking until well done. Cook in at least a 5-quart pot.
Serve with corn bread, green salad and tea.
This will make a complete meal.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Bring to boil lemon juice, sugar and water.
Mix gelatin in cold water; pour into lemon juice mixture.
Let cool completely. Add pineapple and juice, cottage cheese and whipped cream that has been sweetened.
Pour into large mold.
Chill.
To serve, cut in squares.

title: chipmunk pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with eggs.
Add vanilla, apple, nuts and raisins.
Mix.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Combine venison, egg, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, onion or dry onion soup and oatmeal. Mix well. Cook in loaf pan at 350° until done, about an hour. Mix brown sugar and ketchup together. Put on top of meat loaf. Place in oven for 5 minutes more.

title: beef 'n beans
directions: Brown ground beef; salt to taste and drain.
Mix all ingredients in a 1 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nacho salad
directions: Place nacho chips in glass baking dish.
Dip teaspoons of Cheez Whiz over chips.
Add peppers over this.
Place, covered, in microwave 1 1/2 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Set
oven at 375°.
Mix sugar, flour, spice and salt in a 3-quart mixing bowl.
Add the pumpkin, milk and egg and stir until smooth.
Pour
into
the unbaked shells.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes, or until a knife comes out clean 2-inches from edge. Serve warm or cold.
One pie serves 6.

title: mixed pickles(looks like grammy williamson's mustard pickles)
directions: In saucepan, blend mustard with a little vinegar; stir in remaining vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed, cloves and turmeric.
Cover; heat to boiling.
Add cucumbers and remaining vegetables.
Cover; heat just to boiling.
Simmer while quickly packing one clean hot pint jar at a time.
Fill to within 1/2-inch of top making sure vinegar solution covers vegetable. Cap each jar at once.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath. Makes 8 to 9 pints.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Mix soup and
sour
cream
together.
Tear tortillas in pieces.
In 9 x
13-inch
baking
dish
place
a layer of soup mixture, a layer of tortillas, layer of chicken, then chilies, then onions, then
a
layer
of
shredded cheese.
Repeat this process until all ingredients are used up, ending with cheese. Bake at 325° for
45 minutes.
Serve with extra sour cream, if desired.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, oleo and flavoring; add eggs, one at a time. Add sugar; mix well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add baking powder last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: nannie's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in black skillet.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and butter.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Using the whites of the 3 eggs, make meringue for top of pie.

title: apple bars
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a bowl and mix for pie crust.
Pat about 3/4 of this mixture into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Reserve balance of mixture for topping.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper. Cook macaroni and drain. Add hamburger, macaroni and corn together. Add Prego sauce. Bake at 350°, covered, 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal with melted butter.
Add sugar, powder, salt, eggs and chips.
Line cookie sheet with non-shiny side of aluminum foil.
Put on lowest rack in oven.
Let cookies cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add next six ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cheese.
Serve hot with chips.

title: cran-apple relish
directions: Wash cranberries and apples well.
Cut apples into quarters and remove cores.
Put cranberries and apples through a blender or food processor using medium blade.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: pickled beets
directions: Prepare beets.
Wash; leave roots and 1 inch of stem on.
Cook until done, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Remove skins and cover with vinegar;, add sugar and salt.
Let heat thoroughly; put in jars.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine the corn syrup, sugar and water and boil until a little when tried in cold water forms a hard ball, 254°F.
Add the vanilla and pour into the popped corn from which all hard grains should be removed.
Stir till coated, rub hand with Mazola corn oil and form the corn into medium sized balls, pressing closely together.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix everything together except tomatoes and chill overnight. Add tomatoes before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook the spirals and cool, making sure not to overcook them. Add the Good Seasons Italian dressing and Wish-Bone Italian dressing.
Mix in all the remaining ingredients and grated Parmesan cheese.
Mix well all together in a large bowl.
Let set overnight before serving.

title: stir and drop sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix eggs, sugar, vegetable oil, lemon peel or juice and vanilla thoroughly. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop dough by teaspoon about 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: granny's oyster stew
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan.
Add flour (do not brown, just moisten flour).
Add oysters that you have cut into several pieces.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add mushroom soup.
Stir well.
Add milk and seasonings.
Bring just to a boil.
Serve immediately.

title: sausage corn bread
directions: Brown sausage in medium skillet (cast iron); do not drain. Add mangoes and onion.
Mix corn bread mix, egg, sugar and milk until blended well.
Pour over sausages in skillet; bake at 350° until brown.
Invert on plate and top with cheese.

title: baked shrimp dip
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients except snack.
Spoon into small ovenproof bowl.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve with snack.
Makes 2 1/3 cups dip.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix onion, egg, tomato sauce, dry onion soup, oatmeal and hamburger.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour. When it is finished, add ketchup to the top and serve.

title: peanut butter chocolate krispies
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar (almost to boiling).
Add peanut butter.
Turn off heat and add Rice Krispies and stir until coated. Put in buttered cake pan and allow to cool.

title: faye's glazed pecans
directions: Combine sugar and sour cream in a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (240°).
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Continue stirring until mixture begins to cool.
Add pecans, mixing well.
Place individually on waxed paper; cool completely.

title: potluck potato casserole(serves a group!)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour into large baking dish. Sprinkle with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° covered for 30 to 45 minutes (uncover for the last 5 to 10 minutes).

title: busy day soup
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off grease.
Add water, soup mix, tomato sauce and spices.
Boil 5 to 10 minutes to thaw soup mix. Serve.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix by hand.
Make into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.

title: grits casserole(also known as cheese grits)
directions: Cook grits in salted water according to the directions on the package.
When the grits are done, add cheese and butter.
Combine cream with egg yolks and garlic powder, mixing well.
Stir into grits.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and whole orange (be sure to remove orange seeds first).
Add sugar and let stand.

title: meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add green peppers and cook slowly until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until thick enough for serving.
Skim off excess fat before canning. Pour hot into jars, leaving 1-inch head space.
Adjust caps. Process pints 1 hour and quarts for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: seafood salad
directions: Marinate potatoes by tossing with French dressing.
Chill potatoes and seafood thoroughly.
Mix together lightly with pickles and mayonnaise.
Arrange lettuce on serving plates.
Heap salad in mounds on lettuce.
Surround with tomato wedges and eggs.
Top each mound with olives.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Perk in percolator (brown sugar, cloves and cinnamon go in the basket).

title: no sugar cookies(for diabetics)
directions: Pour 1/2 cup boiling water over raisins.
Let stand. Thoroughly cream butter, Sucaryl and beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to butter mixture; add raisins, vanilla, toasted oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet. Cook 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: penne pasta casserole
directions: Cook Penne pasta noodles.
Brown ground beef.
In a greased lasagna pan mix noodles, ground beef, Ragu sauce, cheese soup, and 8 oz. Mozzarella cheese.
Cover pan with foil and bake 30 - 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and sprinkle the rest of the Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: cream of broccoli potato soup
