directions: Cook broccoli, potatoes and onions until tender.
Drain all but 1 cup of broth.
Place 3/4 of the broccoli, potatoes and onions into blender.
Puree.
Return to pan and add milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted and soup is heated through. If soup is too thin, thicken with a bit of cornstarch dissolved well in warm water.
Serve with croutons.

title: pecan cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 egg.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Sprinkle with pecans.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar, corn syrup, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3 eggs.
Pour over mixture in crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until top is firm.
Cool and refrigerate before serving.
The best of two favorites, cheesecake and pecan pie.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken mixture in deep-dish pie crust.
Turn 9-inch pie crust upside-down over the deep dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: date nut crumb roll
directions: Roll crackers into fine crumbs.
Whip the whipping cream and combine 1/2 of crumbs, dates, nuts, vanilla and marshmallows. Form into roll; roll in remaining crumbs.
Chill.
Slice.

title: puppy chow
directions: Warm and mix margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter until smooth and completely melted.
Pour over Crispix cereal. Gently stir until cereal is covered.
Pour into a large grocery bag with powdered sugar.
Shake until well coated.

title: western barbecued beans
directions: Cook ground beef, salt, pepper and garlic in oil until brown. Add other ingredients and bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: country skillet gravy
directions: Spoon flour into hot meat drippings. Blend over low heat until smooth. (You can brown it if you like brown gravy.) Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened. Season with salt and pepper.

title: ranch style beans for fifty
directions: Wash beans.
Add boiling water.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour or longer.
Add bacon to beans.
Add additional water to cover.
Cook slowly until tender, about 1 hour.
Soak chili peppers in warm water.
Remove seeds.
Add pods to beans.
Add tomatoes and other seasonings.
Cook slowly in kettle an additional 2 hours or pour into a 12 x 20 x 4-inch baking pan and bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: grams stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Mix hamburger, rice, eggs, and seasoning together.
Stuff cabbage shell with mixture.
Place in pot.
Add tomato soup and water.
Simmer for at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Follow directions on graham cracker crumb box to make crust out of graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and margarine.
Press in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Beat 2 c. powdered sugar, 2 eggs, and 2 sticks margarine for 10 minutes.
Pour on top of crumbs.
Layer bananas, crushed pineapple, and top with cool whip.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, buttermilk, eggs and extract.
Mix well, then add pecans, coconut and melted butter.
Mix well and pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baby wipes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pour over each section of paper towel.
Squeeze out excess liquid; put in airtight container.
If wipes dry out, repeat first 3 ingredients.

title: mahimahi with mushroom sauce
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on fillets.
Coat with flour. Pan-fry in butter until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in a large pot in the quart of water until slightly tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook slowly until all seasonings are tender.
Add parsley just before serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Spread chicken over broccoli.
Mix soup and mayonnaise together. Slowly blend in milk.
Pour over chicken.
Add crumbled bread over sauce layer.
Spread cheese over bread.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Pour grape jelly and mustard over cocktail smokies and bake in slow oven until glazed well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: san antonio salad
directions: Combine lettuces, artichoke hearts, hearts of palms, onion, pimento, salt and pepper in salad bowl.
Add Parmesan cheese; toss to mix well.

title: ham stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Finely chop stems and onion.
Saute in butter until tender, but not browned.
Add ham, bread crumbs and pimiento.
Stir until combined and crumbs are soft.
Place mushroom caps in buttered baking dish; spoon ham mixture into caps.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: raisin-pineapple muffins
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, juice and orange peel.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir into juice mixture until moistened.
Spoon batter into six muffin cups coated with a cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack; serve warm.
Makes 6 large muffins.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients thoroughly.
Add the next 4 ingredients;
mix thoroughly.
Add nutmeg, cinnamon (optional) and vanilla
(optional).
The	dough may be rolled and cut or made as	biscuits
by
hand.
Bake at
425° until as brown as desired.

title: triple baked beans
directions: Slightly drain beans and mix the tomato and catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Place in a shallow dish.
Top with crumbled bacon, onion and grated cheese.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: gourmet vegetable salad
directions: Drain peas, carrots and beets and dice them.
Put in a bowl with celery and pickles.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice and mix with vegetables.
Sprinkle dill weed to taste and for color.
The amounts of mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice may be varied to your taste.
Serves 6.

title: sugar peanuts
directions: Place in large skillet.
Stir with wooden spoon over medium heat.
When tiny bit of liquid is left, spread nuts on cookie sheet.
Place in 250° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: christmas white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add slightly beaten eggs, gradually mixing well after each addition.
Beat in salt and orange juice. Add flour, a cupful at a time, mixing well.
Combine fruits with batter.
Add nuts and mix well into batter.
Grease baking pans, then line with foil.
Fill with batter.
Bake at 375° about 2 hours for smaller loaf pans and 2 1/2 hours for larger loaf pans. You may also use a ring pan.
Cool thoroughly, then remove from pan.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa together in a large bowl.
Add oil and hot water.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a buttered and floured cake dish. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine sugar, flour and milk.
Microwave 2 minutes on Roast. Beat well and cook 1 1/2 to 2 minutes more (or until mixture thickens).
Add butter and beat until smooth.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Add vanilla and beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy.

title: bean dip for tortilla chips
directions: Bring to boil.
Remove and add 1 (8 ounce) package of shredded cheese.
Let melt and stir.

title: dilly beans
directions: Wash beans, snap top and tails and wash again in several changes of cold water.
Pack beans lengthwise in sterilized quart jars.
Place garlic and dill in each jar.
Add 1 hot pepper if desired.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, oil, eggs, flour, zucchini and 1 teaspoon of the vanilla.
Mix well. Add salt, soda, baking powder and rolled oats.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in walnuts.
Spoon into a greased 15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool in pan.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: corn-bacon bake
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon finely; set aside.
Stir together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in corn meal; add buttermilk and reserved drippings and bacon.
Mix well; pour into well greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown. Cool; invert.
Cut into thin slices.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: mom's warm potato salad
directions: In a large pot, boil the potatoes with the skins on for 10 to 15 minutes until tender. Let the potatoes cool just to the touch and cut into cubes. In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Add potatoes and mix gently. Serve at room temperature.

title: cheese ball
directions: Take out half of chopped beef.
Mix all other ingredients. Roll ball in reserved beef.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Bake cake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes or until done.
(Cake will be thin.)
Mix together until fluffy and smooth 1 small box instant vanilla pudding, 1 cup milk, 8 ounce package softened cream cheese and 8 ounce package Cool Whip.
Top cake with mixture.
Add chopped walnuts, cherries and pineapple.
Rich and delicious.
Keep cool until serving.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape in small ball, pat 1/2 teaspoon peanut butter on each cookie.
Put cookie in top and seal edges with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: jana's dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for the frosting. Spread on jelly roll pan (cookie sheet with sides). Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. When cool, frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: scotch cookies
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Roll in small walnut sized balls and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes or until puffed up cookies flatten.
Remove from pan immediately; cool on wire racks.

title: busy woman peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a baking dish.
Mix in bowl the flour, sugar, oil and milk.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top and bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: cheese dollars
directions: Sift
flour, salt
and	red
pepper
together.	Cut
in margarine; add Tabasco
sauce, Rice Krispies and cheese.
Work with hands until
mixture
sticks
together.
Shape into small balls and flatten to 1/4
inch thickness.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 70 to 100 cheese dollars.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, hot water and salt in 2-quart saucepan. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
After mix comes to a boil, cook without stirring to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot mixture slowly into the egg whites while beating constantly.
Add vanilla and beat until candy forms soft peaks and begins to lose gloss.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef in a skillet until done.
Add onions and celery.
Cook 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Put in covered dish and bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hot spice pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In a 9-inch square pan, melt butter. Stir in pecans. Roast 30 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Mix soy sauce, salt and Tabasco. Stir well. Drain on paper towels. Serve.

title: first prize beans
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Drain. Put beans in a large pot and add fresh water to a depth of 3-inches above the beans.
Stick cloves into peeled onion and add to bean pot with bay leaf and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Boil rapidly 5 minutes. Skim foam from top of beans.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are tender but not mushy.
Drain and reserve liquid.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Use half ham (butt section will have more meat).

title: dot's spanish omelet(breakfast or brunch)
directions: Beat these first 3 ingredients together well.
Grease both sides of an omelet pan lightly with margarine and place over medium heat.
Divide egg mixture in half and pour part in each side of the omelet pan.

When 3/4 of the way done, spoon some Prego sauce (with meat), grated sharp Cheddar cheese, some chopped onion and some chopped green pepper over each side of the divided omelet. Then, flip omelet over, and cook a few seconds, more, so that the Prego sauce and other ingredients have a chance to warm through, thoroughly.
Place on dish and enjoy!

title: deviled brussels sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts as directed on package.
Drain, leaving 1/2 cup water in pan.
Combine all ingredients; simmer 2 to 3 minutes and serve hot.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese together. Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Shape into long rolls with a diameter about the size of a half dollar. Wrap in wax paper or plastic wrap. Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight. Slice thin and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden. This freezes well. Dough may be kept in the fridge for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: curry-glazed sole(or any good whitefish)
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash fillets; dry with paper towels. Arrange in single layer, slightly overlapping, in greased, shallow baking dish.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sour cream, onion and curry powder.
Spread evenly over sole.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily and starts to brown.

title: stroganoff
directions: Mix hamburger, soup and water over heat until hot.
When ready to serve, add sour cream and serve over noodles.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into loaf pans (greased and floured) at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° for 30 minutes or until set in center.
To make round bread, grease and flour tall tomato juice cans.
Mint flavored chocolate chips are also excellent at Christmas.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Spoon into large frying pan with 1/3 cup oil until golden brown.

title: italian cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, olives, green pepper, pimento and onion in a bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Chill for 1 hour or longer before serving.

title: quick chili
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and green pepper in Dutch oven. Cook over medium heat until beef is brown, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain!
Add soup, tomatoes, beans, chili powder, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir well. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle each serving with Cheddar cheese.

title: meringue torte
directions: Beat until stiff the egg whites, cream of tartar and pinch of salt.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Pour into 2 well-greased cake pans.
Bake at 275° for 1/2 hour.
Turn off oven and leave in oven overnight.
Next morning, prepare 2 envelopes Dream Whip according to directions.
Stir in 4 large crushed Heath bars which had been prefrozen for easy crushing.
Ice the meringues as a cake.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 8 hours before serving as cake slices.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients except pecans.
Mix well.
Form into a ball.
Place on waxed paper and chill.
Roll cheese ball into finely chopped pecans.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add noodles, juice and seasonings. Cover and simmer 1/2 hour until noodles are done.
Add mushrooms and sour cream; stir easy.
Cook until heated.

title: baked fish in cheese sauce
directions: Cut fillets into serving pieces.
Arrange in a single layer in greased 2-quart baking dish.
In saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbly.
Add salt, dry mustard, dill and cayenne.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Mix in 1 cup of cheese, stirring until melted.
Mix in shrimp.
Pour sauce over fish and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until top browns and fish flakes easily when tested with fork.

title: microwave hot crab dip
directions: Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: brazilian black beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Rinse well.
In a large pan, add enough water to cover beans about 1 inch.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 3 hours.

title: chicken wreath
directions: Unroll crescent rolls - separate.
On a round cookie sheet place unrolled rolls in the shape of a ring - wide part in center - overlapping, small points to the outside.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Fold point back over chicken mixture making a wreath. Brush with egg white.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: adam's nachos
directions: Get Mommy to drive you to store to buy stuff for nachos.
Wear clothes that she don't mind getting dirty.
Get Mommy to sit you up on table with your nacho stuff around.
Put the nachos on plate (I like a lot of them).
Pour salsa on nachos.
Be careful or it will all go on one spot.
Put cheese on top and try to get it even.
Get Mommy to put them in microwave and let you push the buttons.
It takes about 45 seconds for the cheese to melt.
Goes really good with iced milk.

title: classic karo pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Bake in 3 cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake is done in center.

title: low carb sugar-free ketchup(makes 24 ounces)
directions: Put all ingredients into a saucepan and simmer slowly for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often. It will thicken like the store bought stuff. Take off heat and cool. Stir in 2 packages Splenda. Pour into a jar. Keeps 4 months in the fridge.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix in a large bowl and beat the cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in condensed milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or overnight. Top with desired amount of pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: In skillet, saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in the soup, mushrooms, pimentos and basil.
Set aside.
In a large bowl combine egg noodles, chicken and cheeses.
Add mushroom mixture and mix well. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Chop apples and stir in sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add Wesson oil, soda, egg, flour and nuts last.
Bake in loaf pan 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in pecans.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apple pie filling over warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples. Combine sour cream and egg.
Drizzle over apples.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Great with vanilla ice cream.

title: hot dog snacks
directions: Cut each hot dog into 4 pieces.
Cut bacon into 3 pieces. Wrap bacon around hot dog and secure with a toothpick.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Pack in fairly tight.
Cover with a 1/2-inch of brown sugar packed down.
Cover with
aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry upside down cake
directions: In a small saucepan, melt 2 tbsp. butter; stir in brown sugar.
Spread in ungreased 8 in. baking dish.
Arrange blueberries in a single layer over brown sugar mixture.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl cream remaining ingredients and beat in sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Carefully pour over blueberries.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Immediately invert on a serving platter. Serve with whipped topping if desired.

title: indonesian fried rice
directions: In electric skillet, brown onion in a little oil.
Add pork or shrimp; brown.
Add frozen vegetables, celery and scallions. Simmer for a few minutes.
Add Arturo's sauce; stir good.
Add cooked rice; mix and let simmer until rice is hot.
Add soy sauce. Garnish with scrambled egg, cut in strips or pieces.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Spoon into large bowl.
Brown hash brown potatoes with onion in large skillet, stirring frequently.
Add to sausage; mix well. Scramble eggs in skillet until done to taste, stirring frequently. Add to sausage mixture.
Add chopped green chiles, salt, pepper, salsa and shredded cheese.
Mix well.
Place 2 tablespoons mixture along one side of each tortilla; roll to enclose filling.
Serve with additional salsa.
Makes 24 servings.

title: ham-n-cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Mix ham, vegetables and Parmesan cheese in plate.
Stir Bisquick, milk and eggs with fork until blended.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spaghetti primavera
directions: Cut tofu into pieces 2 x 1/2 x 1/8-inch.
Marinate for 2 hours in bowl with soy sauce, 2 tablespoons oil and vinegar.
Brown the tofu lightly in leftover marinade plus 2 tablespoons oil; set aside.
In boiling water, cook until tender broccoli, fresh or frozen.
Reserve water.
You may substitute 2 cups broccoli and 2 cups asparagus for the 4 cups broccoli.

title: mushroom hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix well the vinegar, soy sauce and sugar.
Pour over the mushrooms and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Marinate 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from sauce and serve.

title: baked chicken-mushroom gravy
directions: Skin
chicken
pieces;	coat
with
flour that has been seasoned.
Put
in	a 13 x 9-inch dish.
In a saucepan combine oleo
and
flour;
brown slightly.	Add soup and water to make gravy consistency.	Add bell pepper, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken.	Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve gravy over rice.

title: s'mores cookie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Press cookie dough into 2 ungreased 12-inch pizza pans.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden. In medium sized saucepan, melt chips with Eagle Brand milk. Spread over crusts.
Sprinkle with milk chocolate candies, marshmallows and peanuts. Bake 4 minutes or until marshmallows are lightly toasted.
Cool.
Cut in wedges.

title: cheese noodle beef casserole
directions: Set aside the cooked noodles. Brown hamburger and onion; drain. Add tomato sauce and vegetables. In a 2-quart casserole, mix cottage cheese and sour cream. Layer noodles, meat and cottage cheese/sour cream. Repeat until all is used. Cover with Cheddar cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble and fry sausage or ham.
Drain well on paper towels. Beat eggs in a small bowl and add milk.
Blend.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put crescent rolls in a 9 x 12-inch pan (use nonstick spray).
Layer sausage over crescent rolls.
Place hash browns over sausage.
Put Cheddar and Velveeta cheese over hash browns.
Pour egg mixture evenly over cheese.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cheese will be golden.
Egg mixture will be cooked up. If it is runny, then longer.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to 255°.
Beat egg whites stiff. Pour syrup mixture in a fine stream into egg whites while beating with electric mixer.
Add vanilla and continue to beat.
Beat by hand until mixture begins to lose gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: texas cabbage casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet, brown sausage.
Add onion and pepper. Saute and drain.
Add cabbage and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer over low heat until cabbage is tender.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet.
In hot oil, saute rice over medium heat, stirring with a metal spoon about 5 minutes or until golden.
Stir eggs into rice; cook, stirring constantly and over medium heat until eggs are cooked, about 3 minutes.
Stir in bacon, soy sauce and pepper; combine well.
Garnish with green onions.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add remaining ingredients and shape into small crescents.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 20 minutes at 325°.
Roll in extra confectioners sugar while warm.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in a greased 2-quart casserole.
In a saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until thick. Fold in cheese.
Pour over cabbage.

title: zucchini hater's casserole
directions: For Oven:
Cook sliced zucchini in salted water.
Drain and mash.
Add sour cream, eggs, cracker crumbs and Cheddar cheese. Put in buttered 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: cocktail ham roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, grated onion and enough mayonnaise to make spreading consistency.
Separate sliced ham.
Spread mixture on slices and place an asparagus spear on ham and roll.
Cut each roll into 4 pieces.
Spear each piece with a toothpick for serving.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Cook shrimp in olive oil until pink.
Add vermouth, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until liquid is almost gone.
Sprinkle on parsley and lemon juice.
Serve over rice.

title: blueberry chiffon pie
directions: Drain blueberries.
Boil juice.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and jello. Add Cool Whip and evaporated milk with 2 tablespoons of sugar. Fold blueberry mixture into whipped milk.
Add berries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Place the sliced beets in a shallow casserole dish.
Melt the butter in a saucepan, add the mustard, honey and Worcestershire sauce.
Season with salt and paprika; heat well.
Pour the sauce over the beets in the casserole dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Measure dry ingredients in a bowl.
Mix oil and water into dry.
Mix well and knead until well blended.
Keep in a sealed container.
Refrigerate after using.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar.
Add egg; beat well. Sift together soda, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar to mixture.
Add banana and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While hot, spread with butter; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: golden wassail
directions: Pour juices into 20 cup electric percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in basket.
Allow to go through perk cycle.
Serve hot.
Yields 20 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter into square pan 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
In smaller bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle mixture over batter.
Pour hot water over top; do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes, or until center is almost set.
Let stand 15 minutes; spoon into dessert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart
casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and 1/2 can of the fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and then stir.
Sprinkle remaining onions on top and bake for additional 5 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove and add the remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool.
May be frozen in airtight container.

title: pate beau monde
directions: Mix several hours before serving. Serve with crackers or thin sliced bread or toast.
Beau Monde is a Spice Island product.

title: savory grilled chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour over chicken in large bowl. Turn to coat; refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Put all in oven to bake.
Can be grilled.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: low-fat ground beef casserole
directions: Mix ground beef with a fork to separate in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle cornstarch or flour on top lightly.
Spread mixed vegetables over top of beef layer.
Add enough water to come halfway up on beef layer.
Spread mashed potatoes over top of vegetables, using a cake decorator to make fancy decorations on top.
Cook in microwave 5 minutes, then move to oven at 400° to brown top of potatoes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Separately combine second five ingredients.
Mix together the wet and dry mixtures and pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 90 minutes at 325°.

title: rice krispie topped brownies
directions: Cream together melted oleo, sugar, cocoa and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs, flour and salt to mixture.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread with jar of marshmallow cream.

title: italian broccoli
directions: Partly defrost broccoli.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil and butter.
Cut garlic in half and saute until golden.
Remove garlic; spread broccoli in a single layer in pan.
Saute, turning gently for 10 minutes, until tender.
Arrange in heatproof serving dish.
Sprinkle with cheese; place under broiler for 1 minute. Serves 6 to 8.

title: german bean soup
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Drain, rinse and cover with fresh water.
Add the ham bone and simmer until beans are soft.
Skim off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are almost soft.
Remove ham bone and return picked meat to soup.

title: louisiana crunch cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and stick of soft margarine with mixer, then add cup of nuts.
Press mixture in lightly greased cookie sheet.
Mix cream cheese and 2 eggs; beat on low speed.
Add confectioners sugar.
Mix well and pour over the first mixture, spreading evenly.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: lemon lush
directions: Cream cheese and gradually add sugar until all sugar is dissolved.
Stir in whipped topping and mix well.
Layer cream cheese mixture and pie filling onto cooled crust.

title: spicy short-n-bread nuggets
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Make a ball; knead until smooth.
Cut into 12 parts.
Out of each part, make a 10-inch rope on floured surface.
Cut into 1/2-inch nuggets.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°, until edges are firm and bottoms brown lightly.
Remove cookies and cool on paper towels.

title: sesame-cheddar scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a large baking sheet.
In a large bowl stir together the flour, cornmeal and baking powder. Add the shortening and butter and blend with your fingers until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Mix in the cheese.

title: nancy's chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add eggs, oil, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in boiling water. (Batter will be thin.)
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil first 4 ingredients and cook 2 minutes.
Add red food coloring; cool.
Place strawberries in pie shell and pour mixture over berries.
Let pie stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: velvet salad
directions: Mix dry jello, pineapple, sour cream, Cool Whip and nuts together.
Chill in mold before serving.

title: cherry-topped cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Measure out 1 cup of dry cake mix; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together remaining dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil (mixture will be crumbly).
Press crust mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 of the way up the sides of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In the same bowl, blend cream cheese and sugar together.
Add 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
At low speed, add milk, lemon juice and vanilla extract; mix until smooth.
Pour into crumb crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes or until center is firm.
Cool to room temperature.
Spoon cherry filling over cheesecake.
Cover and chill 1 hour before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: better potatoes
directions: Mix beer, onion (diced), garlic powder, oregano and basil and store in refrigerator 12 more hours.
Dice 4 to 6 large potatoes in pot and fill 1/2 way with mixture.
Add butter and cover slightly with water.
Boil until potatoes are done.
Drain and serve as is, mashed or whipped.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Slice Italian bread about 1 to 1 1/2 inches thick and line pan.
In a bowl, mix eggs, milk, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bread and let soak 4 to 24 hours.
Cover and refrigerate, turn bread over after several hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli about 20 minutes, seasoned with salt and pepper. Drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and cook in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: 100,000 frosting
directions: Put in pan flour, milk and salt.
Cook until thick.
Cool, then beat a little before adding sugar, soft oleo and Crisco.
Beat sugar, oleo and Crisco real good until thick; add vanilla.

title: barley soup
directions: Melt the margarine in soup pot.
Add barley, celery and onion and cook, stirring constantly, until the barley is slightly transparent.
Stir in the flour.
Add hot chicken broth.
Simmer covered, stirring occasionally for 1 hour or until barley is tender.
Add the cream just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate over low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat chocolate mixture into eggs; add vanilla.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: london broil
directions: Marinate meat in mixture overnight.
Broil in oven or cook on grill, until desired doneness.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Mix juices and Sprite.
Add sherbet before serving.

title: sour cream cookies(club member: laine shoemake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add egg and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill 1 hour at least.
Very important. Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle sugar on top of cookies before baking.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place the cookies in a tight container to keep crisp.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Rinse and put into pot. Simmer 6 to 8 hours in a crock-pot.

title: indian shrimp curry
directions: Saute onion in the butter in top of double boiler over direct heat until tender. Stir in flour, curry powder, salt, sugar and ginger. Add bouillon cube, dissolved in boiling water and milk and cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add shrimp from which black vein has been removed and the lemon juice. Heat well and serve with rice. Serves 6 generously.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar together.
Gradually add sugar, beating after each addition.
Fold in soda crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Place in a buttered pie pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until light brown.

title: tropical fruit smoothie
directions: Put fruit in blender.
Add equal parts water and ice to cover fruit.
Blend until smooth and serve!

title: german stollen
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine yeast, 2 cups of flour and cardamon.
Heat milk, butter, sugar and salt just until warm, stirring occasionally to melt butter.
Add to dry mixture in bowl; add egg.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 1 minute, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
By hand, stir in fruits and peel (or extract).
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough that is easy to handle.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from draft until double, about 1 3/4 hours.

title: steak bake
directions: Toss steak with flour, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Cover.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: fresh spinach and basil salad
directions: Toss spinach and basil together in large bowl.
Saute garlic in olive oil over medium heat.
(Do not let garlic brown.) Sprinkle salad with vinegar.
Pour garlic mixture over salad and toss.
Serve salad and add roasted pine nuts individually. Sprinkle with cheese and fresh ground pepper.
Serves 6.

title: sweet tater casserole
directions: Mash sweet taters; stir in 1/2 cup of brown sugar.
Beat egg and add milk and orange juice.
Stir in sweet tater; mix gradually and add cinnamon.
Put in casserole; dot butter.
Sprinkle the remaining brown sugar and top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch
pan.
Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in a large bowl with wooden spoon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in pan.
Bake until a wooden toothpick comes out clean when inserted, about 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix with heavy mixer the oleo, flour, sugar and butter flavoring.
Roll teaspoonful size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; press center with thumbprint.
Spoon tiny amount of colored jellies or pecan halves in the center.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
They are not brown.
They get a golden color and brown on the bottom.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; boil for 3 minutes. Cool. Add lemon juice to bananas; add pineapple juice. Mix well with sugar mixture. Freeze. Mash until mushy; add carbonated water just before serving.

title: pineapple angel food cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pineapple with juice in a large bowl. Beat with mixer until well blended. Pour batter into an ungreased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly touched. Invert and cool before removing from pan.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: For extra flavor, add recreation and a dash of happy memories. Stir well and remove any specks of jealousy, temper and criticism.
If you like a sweeter product, add generous portion of love.
Keep warm with a steady flame of devotion.
Never serve with cold shoulder or hot tongue.
Add to this recipe the presence and love of God and you will have quite a home.

title: dyno-mite coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed; add coconut flavoring and 1/2 bag of coconut.
Bake as directed until done (takes longer because of coconut).
Add water to evaporated milk to make 2 cups and add sugar.
Punch holes in cake as soon as it is done and pour milk/sugar over cake while still hot.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, spread crushed pineapple and juice on top, Cool Whip and finally, rest of coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: new england yam bake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with pineapple.
Arrange yams in dish.
Pour reserved syrup over yams.
Sprinkle nuts over yams.
Combine dry ingredients and cut in margarine until a coarse texture.
Top yams with dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and brown lightly.
Yields 6 to 8.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup, corn flakes and almonds. Put in buttered casserole. Pour soup over all then top with corn flakes and almonds.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 min.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix and bring to boil first 4 ingredients.
Add to above mixture remaining ingredients.
Grease large casserole dish with melted butter.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Cook vanilla pudding in 2 cups of the drained fruit juice. If not enough for 2 cups, add a little water.
Add the Tang to cooking pudding.
When pudding is cool, add the fruit and chill in the refrigerator.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda, baking powder and cocoa.
Mix butter and Coke and bring to boil.
Pour over dry mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and marshmallows.
This will be a thin batter. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: one-pot spaghetti
directions: Crumble ground beef into a Dutch oven.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat about 10 minutes or until brown.
Pour into strainer to drain off any fat.
Put beef back into Dutch oven. Wash and chop onion and stir into ground beef.
Add tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce, salt, water and spaghetti.
Heat about 15 minutes or until the spaghetti is tender.
Remove from heat and stir. Sprinkle, just before serving, with Parmesan cheese.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt oleo in large skillet.
Beat eggs and sugar together and add to butter.
Add dates.
Stir constantly and over very low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Put mixture in a bowl and cool .
Make into balls about the size of a quarter and roll in flaked coconut.

title: griddle cakes(pancakes)
directions: Combine well-beaten egg, milk and melted shortening.
Add liquid ingredients to the dry, stirring only until smooth.
Do not overmix; the batter will/should look slightly lumpy.
Stir by hand.
Bake on hot griddle, wiped generously with shortening/oil.

title: popcorn crunch
directions: In medium saucepan, melt vanilla-flavored candy coating over low heat, stirring constantly.
In a very large bowl, combine popped popcorn, candy-coated chocolate or peanut butter-flavored pieces and raisins.
Pour warm, melted coating over popcorn mixture, tossing to coat.
Spread onto a greased cookie sheet. Cool thoroughly.
Break apart.

title: asparagus souffle
directions: Mix everything together except butter.
Pour into greased loaf size pan.
Add cracker or bread crumbs to top and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt shortening and chocolate.
Add sugar and blend.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well!! Add flour and salt.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased pan 30 minutes.

title: pecan logs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Gradually knead enough powdered sugar into mixture until consistency is stiff. Divide mixture into 8 (6-inch) logs.
Wrap each log and freeze for 1 hour.
Combine caramels and milk in saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring often, until mixture is smooth.
Dip logs into caramel mixture and roll in pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Store in refrigerator or freezer up to 1 month.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices to serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Blend.
Mix pumpkin, water and flour.
Add vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Mix and add soda, salt, baking powder, spices and nuts.
Bake in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes or small loaves 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers and clean inside.
Mix rice, tomato sauce, ground beef, salt and pepper and Accent.
Fill peppers with mixture.
Put in large pot.
Pour can of tomatoes and 1 can of water over peppers.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour.

title: puff pizza
directions: Cook meat with onions until done.
Mix sauce and meat and drop in cut up biscuits and mix well.
Add cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Put pepperoni on top; sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni and vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over salad and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: Blend the avocados,
lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Set aside. Mix the mayonnaise,
sour	cream
and taco mix.
Layer bean dip on bottom of pan; continue to layer avocado mix, sour cream mixture, onions,
tomatoes,
olives
and Cheddar cheese. Chill and serve.
Serve with nacho chips, optional.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Grease bottoms of 2 (8 x 4 x 2-inch) loaf pans.
Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips and walnuts.
Blend well on medium speed.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake in center of oven for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: lima beans in tomato and garlic sauce
directions: Put the lima beans in a large pot with about 2 quarts of water and some salt.
Bring the water to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer the beans until they are tender, but don't let them get mushy.
Drain them and save the broth to use in a soup, it's delicious.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onion in butter for 8 minutes.
Add mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream; cook gently for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: stir-fry tofu and veggies
directions: Cut tofu into 1-inch cubes.
In wok or skillet, bring soy sauce, garlic, ginger and wine to a boil.
Add tofu cubes, cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove tofu and remaining broth from wok or skillet.
Heat oil in wok and stir-fry vegetables over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add remaining broth, tofu and cashews or almonds.
Heat and serve.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, bell pepper, celery, onion, salt and pepper. Then add cracker crumbs.
Mix milk, eggs and 1 can tomato sauce in a bowl and then pour into the meat mixture.
Take half grated cheese and mix with meat.
Form loaf with meat mixture.
Pour remaining can of tomato sauce on top of loaf when the loaf is well done.
Sprinkle remaining grated cheese on top of loaf.
Remove from oven when cheese is melted.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Bake shell.
Heat milk and margarine to boiling.
Combine brown sugar, flour, egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix with small amount of warm milk.
Continue to cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Pour in shell.
Mix egg whites with sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar and salt to make meringue.

title: italian meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large nonstick skillet, brown the beef over medium heat and drain well.
Add the onion, bell pepper and garlic and cook, stirring, 5 minutes.
Dissolve the cornstarch in the water and add to the skillet along with the tomato paste and all the seasonings.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle half of the Parmesan cheese over the bottom of the pie shell.
Cover with half of the meat mixture, then half of the Mozzarella.
Layer with the remaining meat and the Parmesan cheese.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with the Mozzarella and return to oven until the cheese melts, about 5 more minutes.
Makes 6 servings. Fat, 16 g.

title: barbecued chicken pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°. In a small bowl, combine chicken and barbecue sauce; mix well. Place bread shell on ungreased pizza pan. Spread chicken mixture over shell. Arrange tomatoes over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and dried basil. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bread shell is browned. If you would like, sprinkle with cilantro.

title: taco casserole
directions: Reserve a few pieces of olives and celery for garnishing the top of casserole. Brown turkey or ground beef and celery in nonstick skillet. Do not drain grease.
Pour in taco seasoning, olives and mushrooms. Heat until seasoning is dissolved.

title: heavenly carrots
directions: Boil carrots until crisp-tender in salted water.
Place cooked carrots, peppers and onion, in layers and cover with sauce, which is made by blending well the remaining ingredients.

title: vanilla no-bake cookies
directions: Stir the margarine and sugar over medium-high heat until full boil is reached; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add the oats, coconut and vanilla chips.
Also add the vanilla and food coloring as desired.
Quickly drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to cool. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: pico
directions: Dice tomatoes, onions and jalapenos. Mix together. Pick the cilantro leaves from stems. Chop leaves. Use about 1/4 cup cilantro. Mix all together. Squeeze juice from lime. Add salt, to taste. Refrigerate for a few hours before eating.

title: date nut roll
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter, and salt until ball is formed. Then beat in dates and nuts. Pour onto sheet of wax paper. Roll into log form. May need to use towel to protect hands from heat. Slice after cooled.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Lightly pile in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Cook at 400° about 25 minutes.
If you add more chicken, add more celery.

title: oreo balls
directions: Mix together Oreos and cream cheese until you have a large ball.
Make tiny balls (dime size).
Cool in refrigerator.
Dip into melted almond bark and sprinkle with festive sprinkles before balls dry.

title: dill dip (served in pumpernickel loaf)
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
This needs to
sit
in refrigerator
for
at
least 3 hours
(preferably
overnight). Take a 2 pound round loaf of pumpernickel bread and
hull
out the center of the loaf.
Cut this center portion of
the
loaf into bite size cubes and place around the loaf.
Now
fill the loaf with
the dill dip.
Use bread cubes to dip.
I
usually buy an extra 1 pound loaf to cube ahead of time and place in a Ziploc bag.
This
will
serve a large crowd.
Garnish with a sprig of fresh dill.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon.
Add egg, cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and onion. Make into patties and fry slowly until brown.
Use only enough grease to keep from sticking.

title: italian pizzilla
directions: Mix melted butter, oil, and sugar.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Then fold in flour.
Mix well.

title: party punch recipe
directions: Before serving, add the ginger ale.
Serve.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage or bacon; drain well.
Crumble sausage or bacon.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Place bread cubes in the bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish, then sausage or bacon, then cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by scoops into hot oil.

title: easy wings
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and pour over the wings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: penuche
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk and cook, stirring only until sugar is dissolved and a little dropped in cold water forms a soft ball (238°).
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm, then beat until mixture begins to hold its shape.
Stir in walnuts and turn into greased pan about 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients. Put into prepared graham cracker crust. Chill until firm.

title: rivel rice potato soup
directions: Cook beef until soft; add diced raw potatoes, rice and rivels.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns. Melt 1 stick of butter. Mix together hash browns, butter, soup, sour cream and cheese. Spread evenly in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Melt 1/2 stick of butter. Add to the cornflakes and stir until cornflakes are coated with butter. Top potatoes with cornflakes. Bake at 375° for about 40 to 45 minutes. These can be made the night before and kept in the refrigerator.

title: fish stew for 35
directions: Fry bacon crisp; save grease.
Crumble bacon.
Pour drippings in bottom of pot.
Place layers of potatoes, onion and fish. Spread bacon unevenly over layers.
Add salt and pepper.
Place layers in this order until you've used them.
Pour 2 cans of tomato juice over ingredients.
Add water.
Cook over medium heat for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
The last hour, lower heat.
The last 10 minutes of cooking, break eggs, one at a time, in top of stew pot. At no time stir this stew.

title: apple pie in a jar
directions: Cook syrup until thick and bubbly and add lemon juice.

title: scallops
directions: Toss scallops in mixture.
Broil 2 1/2 to 4 minutes.
This can also be microwaved.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk in large saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until well melted.
Add uncooked oatmeal and stir, mixing well.
Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let cool.
Enjoy!

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in small ungreased cake pan; spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherry filling. Sprinkle oats and pecans over cake mix.
Pour butter evenly over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: rolls
directions: Mix. Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Let raise 20 minutes.
Butter and shape; let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a cookie sheet with vegetable oil spray.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the margarine with the sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat.
Add flour and mix well.
Mix in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and allow to cool on a rack.
This recipe has 4 grams of fat and 3 milligrams of sodium.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Bring the brown sugar, Spry and butter to a boil. Remove from stove. Add the milk. Bring to a boil and boil exactly 3 minutes. Remove from stove and add the 10x sugar.
Mix with beaters until smooth.
Put on cake.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco together.
Add sugar, one cup at a time, beating after each addition.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients and bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Brown flour in margarine.
Add onions, smoked sausage and garlic.
Saute until onions soften.
Add chicken.
Cover and let steam, but stir often.
Add water, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Let cook until chicken is done.
Turn off burner and add one pinch file.

title: homestyle chicken and biscuit dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in cooking bag (14 x 20-inch).
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add gravy mix, garlic powder and water.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Place carrots and celery in bag in even layer.
Sprinkle chicken with seasonings.
Place on top of vegetables.
Arrange biscuits around chicken. Close bag with nylon tie.
Cut slits on top. Bake until chicken is tender, about 1 hour.

title: cheese soup
directions: In covered saucepan, cook carrots, onion and celery in butter over low heat until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add broth and salt. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in milk and cheese and cook until cheese melts and soup is heated through.
Do not boil.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix dry jello into cottage cheese.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix ans chill.

title: shrimp creole with rice or pasta
directions: Cook shrimp; set aside.
In large skillet, saute onions and garlic in oil for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, pepper, sugar and broth; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add basil and pepper; cook 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water; stir into sauce and cook until thick.
Add shrimp, parsley and green onion.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Serves 4.

title: pumpernickel bread dip
directions: Hollow out one loaf of bread and cut the second loaf into squares.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Place mixture into hollowed loaf.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.
Dip bread squares into mixture.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Cook first four ingredients to a boil for 1 minute and set aside.
Mix pudding and 3 cups milk; fold in Cool Whip.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer graham crackers.
Pour one half of the custard, then line another layer of graham crackers.
Top with the last of the custard and a third layer of crackers.
Cover this with the icing that was made from the first four ingredients. (Takes almost a box of graham crackers.)

title: wild rice with olives
directions: Saute both rices in the 1/4 cup oleo until slightly brown. Chop and saute in 1/4 cup olive oil the onion, green onions and bell pepper.
Add sauteed greens to browned rice.
Add the chicken broth, olives, olive juice, sliced water chestnuts and mushrooms to the rice mixture.
Mix all together and bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan or a 3-quart oblong Pyrex baking dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place a layer of bread, then a layer of chicken.
Alternate layers.
Beat eggs, milk and broth.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the sugar and pineapple juice in bowl and cut bananas first, then other fruit; add.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve in fruit cups or on lettuce leaves.
Top with teaspoon of mayonnaise.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix altogether and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until set.

title: peach puff pie
directions: Cream butter with half the sugar.
Add beaten eggs gradually and lemon rind.
Add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk.
Line a pie plate with pastry.
Put peaches into it with remaining sugar, then spread batter over all and bake at 375° for 20 minutes; then 350° for 20 minutes.
Canned peaches can be used.

title: wassail (christmas drink)
directions: Mix together and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes a delicious holiday drink, "here we go a wassailing."

title: jarrett anderson tartar's salad
directions: Mix container of Cool Whip with crushed pineapple and box of vanilla pudding.
Add colored marshmallows, maraschino cherries cut up in small pieces.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Use whatever amount desired of last three ingredients.

title: cranberry buttermilk scones
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, 1/3 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda; cut in butter.
Stir in the buttermilk just until combined.
Fold in the cranberries and orange peel.
Turn onto a floured surface.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each portion into a ball and pat into a 6 inch circle.
Cut each circle into six wedges. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet and brush with milk.
Combine the cinnamon and remaining sugar; sprinkle over scones.
Bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in ice cream freezer and churn.

title: lazy man's barbecue chicken
directions: Mix ketchup and Coke in skillet. Heat until ketchup is dissolved. Add chicken and cover. Cook over low to medium heat until chicken is done, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dilled broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until crisp (4 to 5 minutes). Drain well and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients with broccoli, stirring gently.
Chill, covered, at least 3 hours.
Serve with sliced eggs and chopped olives as garnish.

title: macaroni and ham salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the boiling water.
Add the 1 cup mayonnaise and mix together thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and place in a salad mold.
Let stand in refrigerator until use.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer at least one hour.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Spray a medium baking dish with Pam.
Place bite size pieces of chicken in bottom of dish.
Mix soup and 1 1/2 cups of broth from cooked chicken; pour over chicken.
Make a batter of 1 stick margarine (melted), 1 cup flour, 1 cup buttermilk and black pepper; pour over top of chicken.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: onion cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add cream cheese, stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water, add to cream cheese mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Yields six (1/2-cup) servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix
sugar
and cornstarch together well.
Add vinegar, cloves,
catsup,
oil, salt, vanilla and beet juice.
Mix well and cook until thick.
Add beets and heat thoroughly.

title: california blend casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until almost tender.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Cut cheese in chunks and mix with vegetables. Melt butter and add crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese is bubbly.

title: souffle sandwich(chicago recipe)
directions: Cut crusts and butter the bread. Place 8 slices, butter side down, in large flat pan. Cover the bread with filling. Cover filling with cheese. Place remaining 8 slices of bread on top of cheese, butter side up. Beat together remaining ingredients and pour over sandwiches. Place in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Top with hot undiluted mushroom soup when serving. Serves 8.

title: cheese hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in ungreased baking pan. Sprinkle cornflake crumbs on top; drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients together. Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except steak in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer gently 5 minutes.
Pound round steak.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Place in a roasting pan or casserole dish. Pour hot sauce over meat.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: shrimp jello mold(serves at least 12)
directions: Turn blender to liquify until everything is well blended. Boil 4 1/2 cups water.
Add 3 large packages lemon jello.
When blended, add part to blender.
Liquify.
Pour extra jello and contents in blender into large pan where first vegetables and shrimp are.
Mix very well.
Chill overnight.
Serve with dab of salad dressing and crackers.

title: delightfully chinese salad
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Toss lightly.
(Best served with "Darlene's Delight" salad oil dressing!)

title: soft-shell tacos
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet until lightly brown.
Add taco seasoning with small amount of water.
Simmer until water is gone; stir occasionally.
Take up into bowl.
Chop or shred onion, tomatoes and lettuce; place in separate small bowls.
May also serve with sour cream and taco sauce.

title: taboulah
directions: Soak the bulgur in lemon juice for 1/2 an hour.
Chop all the first 4 ingredients very fine.
Mix all together.
Add olive oil, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with romaine lettuce!

title: cissy's cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes (enough to fill approximately a 2-quart casserole dish).
Partially boil potatoes and drain.
Let cool.

title: incredible crab
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat over a double boiler or in the microwave until all the cheese is melted and mixture is hot (not boiling).
Pour into a chafing dish and serve hot with crackers.
A great dish for parties!

title: congealed pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding and pineapple; add Cool Whip, cherries and marshmallows.
Put in freezer to firm.
Take out a little while before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice margarine in several pieces and place on bottom of large casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 of stuffing over margarine.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, salt and syrup in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; remove and stir.
Cook 4 minutes; stir.
Add butter and vanilla; blend well.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Mixture should be dark brown.
Add soda; stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet and spread. Let cool; break apart and eat.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Place cut side down in dish in microwave.
Microwave on High, covered, 2 to 3 minutes or cook in boiling water 3 to 4 minutes.
Scoop out pulp, leaving a quarter-inch shell; set aside.
Cook onion in hot oil until tender. Add chopped zucchini and cook 1 minute.
Stir in flour, basil and pepper.
Cook and stir one more minute.
Gradually add zucchini to egg, stir in Parmesan.
Spoon mixture into shells.
Bake in square baking dish, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peach angel food cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, peaches and juice (do not add water).
Mix well.
Pour into tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake according to directions on cake package.
If desired, top with whipped topping.
This is a great tasting super easy low fat/calorie dessert.

title: curried egg sauce
directions: Blend a little White Sauce with the curry powder.
Stir curry powder mixture, parsley and egg into remaining White Sauce.
Good on spinach, broccoli and asparagus.
Yield:
1 1/4 cups.

title: blondie brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine butter and milk in saucepan.
Place on low heat until butter melts. Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar; add egg.
Stir until blended. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into pan.
Bake at 350° for 27 to 30 minutes or until pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: dashi
directions: Wipe konbu with dry cloth lightly.
Do not wipe off the white powdery substance on the surface which is one element that provides a unique savory flavor.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour and salt.
In large heavy sauce pan or skillet, brown beef in oil.
Stir in water, sauce and seasoning. Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and simmer until tender, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pop up rolls
directions: In a bowl, stir together all ingredients until thoroughly combined. Fill greased muffin cups half full. Bake at 375° for 18-20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Spray Pam in an ovenproof frying pan.
Heat pan until it is medium-hot.
Brown pork chops on both sides and remove from pan. Melt margarine in pan.
Brown rice over medium-low heat, stirring to prevent burning.
When brown, take off heat.
Return pork chops. Add soup and 1/2 can of water.
Cover with lid and bake at 350° in oven for 45 minutes to an hour.
When rice has absorbed the soup, it is done.

title: sugar gems
directions: Cream
butter and sugars.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Mix flour, soda
and
salt;
add
to batter.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados and then add all other ingredients.
Place plastic wrap directly on food and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Stir well and serve with chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish - beans, hamburger meat
(cooked with onions), cheese, and cornbread mix
(Mix cornbread pkg. according to instructions and
add
corn).
Bake
for 45 minutes or until done at 350 degrees.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix apple, cinnamon, and sugar on bottom of 8 x 8 dish.
Mix rest of ingredients to crumble stage.
Crumble over apple.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° or until apples are tender, and top is brown.

title: onion pie
directions: Crush crackers in baking dish; add melted margarine to crackers to make the crust on bottom of dish.
Slice onions and saute in frying pan with margarine until white or soft.
Pour onions into dish.
Mix eggs in milk; pour over onions.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cool chicken salad
directions: Cook whole chicken.
Boil until falls easily off the bone. Let cool.
Pull chicken meat off bones and place in bowl.
Prepare lettuce for salad.
Cut up grapes into lettuce.
Place cooled chicken into lettuce and grape bowl.
Mix in mayonnaise to taste. Season with black pepper.
Place in refrigerator and eat when chilled.
Easy and refreshing!

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all of the above thoroughly. drop well apart with 2 inch ice cream scoop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees until brown; remove while centers are still chewy.

title: marble sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine cocoa and 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Beat 1 cup sugar with 1/2 cup butter; add eggs and vanilla.
Alternate dry ingredients with sour cream.
Spread 1/2 of batter in 9-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle with half of cocoa mixture; repeat.
Sprinkle crumb topping over batter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate or 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl until lightly coated with batter.
Pour into greased pan and bake until golden brown at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: dumplings
directions: Blend flour, shortening and salt. Beat egg and add water and egg to flour mixture. Knead and roll out very thin. Cut into squares and drop in chicken broth.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain green beans, pimentos, peas and corn.
Dice pepper, onion and celery.
Mix and cook the remaining ingredients.
Pour the ingredients over the drained and diced vegetables.
Best if left to set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Dissolve yeast in hot water.
Stir in warm water and brown sugar.
Slowly add flour.
Stir until smooth and dough doesn't stick to sides of bowl.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface.
(Put flour on your hands.)

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine; mix with graham cracker crumbs and spread mixture in bottom of an oblong 9 x 13-inch pan for crust. Slice bananas over crust.
Whip 2 sticks margarine, confectioners sugar and eggs for 15 minutes.
This makes sauce.
Pour over bananas.
Drain the pineapple and spread over sauce.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: pytel's post game pot of beans(feeds 4 hungry coaches and friends)
directions: Place baked beans in a large kettle.
Throw in onion that is chopped, barbecue and red hot sauces and heat.
Don't worry about heating to a boil, that's what the cayenne pepper sauce is in for.

title: white cake(fat free)
directions: Spray 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine flour, cornstarch, baking powder and salt. In medium bowl using fork or wire whisk, stir sugar and milk until sugar is almost dissolved.
Add egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla; stir until thoroughly blended.
Gradually add to flour mixture, stirring until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan or wire rack.

title: remainder salad
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling liquid together, then add sherbet. Stir until melted. Add the oranges. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart ring mold. Chill. Unmold and fill center with Ambrosia.

title: ranch mashed potatoes
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cover potatoes with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are very tender; drain.
Return potatoes to saucepan; mash.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: one step chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave-safe casserole dish. Cover; microcook on High 5 minutes.
Stir to break up meat. Microcook additional 20 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Place peppercorns on a work surface or cutting board. Cover them with a paper towel and using a rolling pin or mallet, crunch the peppercorns into coarse pieces. Press the crushed peppercorns onto both sides of steak.

title: lazy gal's casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased casserole. Brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder. Add tomato soup and water.
Mix thoroughly and add rice.
Mix all and pour over cabbage; mix lightly.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into medium bowl.
Cream butter and sugar into large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add flour mixture and apples 1/2 at a time, mixing well after each.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove to wire rack to completely cool.

title: three bean pizza
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion.
Add garlic.
Add beans, salsa and cilantro.
Cook 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare pizza dough. Sprinkle dough with 1/2 grease.
Spoon on mixture on top of cheese. Cover with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: cajun cabbage(serves six.  preparation time:  one hour)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Saute garlic in bacon fat; add onion and saute.
Add bell pepper and continue to saute.
Add cabbage and continue sauteing.
Add tomatoes and one can of water.
Add cayenne pepper and cover.
Simmer for one to three hours, stirring occasionally.
You really can't overcook it.
You may use two large onions, two bell peppers and two cans of tomatoes instead of a can of water.
You can vary this receipt to taste on garlic and cayenne pepper.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add creamed ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hot cheesy almond spread
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except almonds, until well blended. Stir
in
almonds.	Microwave on Medium temperature until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with almonds and serve with crackers.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter.
Sprinkle 1/3 of mixture in 8-inch square pan and cover with half of the blueberries.
Top with half of remaining crumbs, then rest of berries and crumbs. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serve by spooning in individual dessert dish. Top with whipped cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a 4-quart pan; set aside.
In 1-quart bowl, place butter and microwave on High power 30 to 60 seconds or until melted.
Stir in gelatin and corn syrup.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, until mixture comes to a boil, stirring once.
Mix in soda until well blended.
Pour over popcorn.
Toss to coat evenly, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Turn onto wax paper, spread out and allow to cool.
Break into small pieces.
Store in covered container.

title: sauteed dandelion flowers
directions: Do not wash the dandelion flowers, or they will close, so it is important that they are clean when picked.
Heat the butter in a skillet.
Dip each blossom into the beaten eggs, then into flour; saute briefly in the butter.
Season with salt and pepper. Serve as a vegetable or special side dish.
Serves 2.

title: good slaw
directions: Mix to desired consistency.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Place chicken, skin side up, in lightly oiled baking pan.
Pour melted butter over chicken. Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and ginger.
Top with diced celery.
Bake chicken at 325° about 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Drain pineapple juice into a cup.
Blend in brown sugar, water, soy sauce, vinegar and cornstarch.
Pour mixture over chicken in pan.
Continue baking for 45 minutes until chicken is done to your liking.
Top with pineapple chunks and sliced red pepper.
Makes 4 servings.
Good served with buttered rice, steamed broccoli, string beans and a salad.

title: christmas log
directions: Cut up marshmallows and cherries.
Mix raisins, marshmallows, pecans and cherries together.
Warm milk and add to other ingredients.
Form a log from mixture.
Roll in cracker crumbs. Wrap in wax paper and put in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Then add nuts and Cool Whip and mix well.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together everything except chips and vanilla.
Then add chips and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: instant cappuccino
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in a tight container.
Put 1 heaping spoonful in 1 cup hot water.

title: conga bars
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar; cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake in a 10-inch square pan in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into 2-inch square bars.

title: apple crisp delight
directions: Cut up apples in baking pan, add sugar.
Mix together cinnamon, butter and flour and pour over apples.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: (cinnamon) baked beans
directions: Mix all together all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a slow oven at 250° for 2 hours or crock-pot for 4 to 6 hours.

title: just soy cheese cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into shallow baking pan and bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Can top with cherry, strawberry, blueberry or raspberry pie mix or one fruit on each square.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; let stand until cold but not thick; add sugar slowly and blend.
In large chilled bowl whip milk until light and fluffy.
Add jello mixture and beat until well mixed.
Add rind and juice of lemon.
Roll cracker crumbs and spread 1/2 of them in bottom of drip pan.
Pour in jello mixture and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: didee chicken
directions: Let sauce boil.
Salt and pepper fryer (also remove skin). Cut fryer in half.
Put into sauce.
Cook with lid on for 45 minutes.
Remove lid and brown.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in beans, apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla (can plump raisins in hot water).
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 or 50 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean. Good with cream cheese icing, powdered sugar, white cooked icing or just whipped cream.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Dilute soup with 3/4 can water.
Heat to boiling. Pour over gelatin and stir until dissolved thoroughly; cool. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into molds and chill. Serve on lettuce leaf and top with mayonnaise. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Make cake as directed on package and split into 4 layers.
Mix coconut, sour cream and sugar.
Frost cake.

title: nanny's sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prepare unbaked pie shell.
Separate eggs (save yolks).
Beat egg whites until stiff (set aside). Blend potatoes, milk, sugar, applesauce, rum flavoring and at least 1 egg yolk (all 3 if you'd like) until smooth; fold in egg whites.
Pour 1/2 mixture into pie shell.
Sprinkle generously spices over mixture.
