Pour remainder of mixture into shell. Sprinkle generously spices over top.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove when toothpick comes out clean.

title: corned beef enchiladas
directions: Heat corned beef in pan.
Heat enchilada sauce and heat oil. Dip corn tortilla in oil to soften, dip in enchilada sauce, put on plate and fill with corned beef and roll.
Top with cheese. Sprinkle on a few teaspoons enchilada sauce.
Top with olives and serve.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Alternate in greased 2-quart baking dish with 8 ounce package cooked noodles.
Top with 3/4 cup crumbs or crushed Wheaties. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: oklahoma baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot about 4 hours on high or in oven at 350° until heated thoroughly.
Reheat leftovers in microwave.

title: cranberry chiffon pie
directions: Place gelatin in custard cup.
Add cold water and let stand for 2 minutes.
Place cup in pan of boiling water until gelatin dissolves.
Add to cranberry sauce which has been crushed with fork.
Add salt, rind and juice; chill mixture begins to set.
Beat egg whites until stiff and beat in sugar.
Fold in cranberry mixture.
Pour filling into baked shell and chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix mashed berries, sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add water, lemon juice and coloring.
Cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thick.
Cool.
Arrange berries in pie crust.
Pour cooked mixture over berries.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, eggs and 2 cups sugar; mix.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and sour cream; mix well (no lumps).
The heavy cream is most important.
You must whip heavy cream until fluffy, then fold into cream cheese.
Mix slowly until well blended.
Set aside.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: In iron
skillet,
saute first 3 ingredients.
Add meat and cook
for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cajun salt
directions: Mix well and keep in airtight container. Do keep a shaker bottle of this on stove.
Use sparingly on all your favorite meats.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, cream cheese, salt and Cheez Whiz in bowl.
Saute onion in butter until brown.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart pan.
Combine sugar and milk. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixtures boil. Cook to soft boil stage (234°).
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into square cake pan.

title: martha washington balls
directions: Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate, using toothpicks and let dry. Freezes well.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Mix crushed Oreo cookies with margarine (save a little for topping).
Place into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put ice cream on top of cookies.
Soften a little, then add chocolate topping. Then Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with remaining crushed Oreos. Freeze.
(Let ice cream soften a little before spreading.)

title: goblin's delight cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, egg, salt, orange peel and food color in a small mixer bowl; beat until smooth.
Add Hershey's chocolate chips; set aside.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Brown meat with celery, onion and green pepper.
Drain grease and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for a few minutes; serve on rolls.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Poke holes in warm cake with a fork.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut together.
Pour over cake.
Top with Cool Whip and flaked coconut.

title: play dough(do not eat this!)
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until a ball forms.
Remove from pan; cool slightly and knead.
Store in airtight plastic containers or in plastic bags.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a buttered casserole.
Blend together sugar, butter and flour.
Cover apples with water and cinnamon.
Now add sugar mixture (just sprinkle over apples).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops braised in white wine
directions: Combine sage, rosemary, garlic, salt and pepper.
Press mixture on both sides of chops.
Melt butter and add oil to 10 to 12-inch skillet using moderate heat.
Add chops and brown for 2 minutes on each side.
Remove from pan.
Pour off excess fat, leaving a light film of fat in pan.
Add 1/2 cup wine.
Bring to a boil.
Return chops to pan.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 25 to 30 minutes, basting with pan juices.
Transfer chops to heated platter.
Pour rest of wine into skillet and boil to reduce slightly.
Pour over chops.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine sugar, flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, allspice, cloves and cinnamon in large bowl.
Mix eggs, pumpkin, oil and water; combine with dry ingredients.
Beat well until mixed.
Fold in pecans and raisins.
Bake in large greased pan.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice in rice cooker.
Cut bacon in pieces and fry.
When bacon is almost done, put in sliced green onions.
Add cooked rice.
Fry on high.
Move rice to the sides.
Fry an egg in the middle.
Mix with rice.
Add soy sauce to your desired taste.

title: buttery cinnamon skillet apples
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat, spooning sauce over apples occasionally, until apples are fork-tender and sauce is thickened (12 to 15 minutes).

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Remove 1 cup of dry cake mix and set aside for topping.
Add egg and melted butter to the rest of the cake mix and mix well. Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: tea balls
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar.
Gradually add flour and salt. Mix well.
Work in vanilla and nuts.
Chill dough.
Form 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets and bake at 370° for 14 to 17 minutes.
While warm, roll in sugar.
Repeat when cold.

title: christmas fruit cake cookies
directions: Knead together eggs, sugar and margarine.
Sift flour and mix with egg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet, sprayed with Pam.
(I shape them in little balls.) Bake at 275° for 25 to 28 minutes.
"Do not overbake." Best after 2 to 3 weeks.
Bake in advance for Christmas!

title: coconut delight
directions: Layer 1: Mix together 1 cup chopped pecans, flour and margarine. Spread into 9X13 inch dish. Bake at 250 degrees for 35 minutes. Cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Add strawberries, bananas, pineapple and pecans.
Divide into half.
Refrigerate 1/2 of mixture until jelled.
Remove from refrigerator.
Top with sour cream.
Pour 1/2 remaining mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate until jelled.

title: golden nugget meatballs
directions: Combine ground
beef,
bread
crumbs,
green pepper, dry mustard, garlic salt, salt, pepper, egg and catsup;
shape into 16 balls (3 to 4 tablespoons per ball).
Place a cheese cube in center,
shaping
meat
around.
Brown in lard;
pour off drippings.
Add
tomato sauce, cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes. Remove
cover
and
continue simmering 5 to 10 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened.

title: bernice's beautiful black cake
directions: Put in saucepan the oleo, water, cocoa and Wesson oil.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
In mixing bowl, add sugar, flour and salt. Pour the cool mixture over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, cinnamon, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
When you remove from oven, have the icing ready.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Add biscuit baking mix; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
At this point you can flatten with a fork and bake or leave and bake as is and insert kisses after they come out. Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
If you leave in ball form, press candy kiss into ball immediately after baking.

title: coconut-caramel no-bake cookies
directions: Mix butter, milk, sugar and salt. Cook 3 to 5 minutes (on low), stirring. Remove. Add caramels. Return to heat until melted. Add vanilla. Add coconut and oatmeal. Mix well. Drop by tablespoons. Refrigerate until set. (Makes 4 1/2 dozen.)

title: ham salad sandwich
directions: Use amounts of each ingredient as desired.
Grind pork roll and pickles.
Add grated cheese.
Add enough salad dressing for desired consistency.
Spread between 2 pieces of bread.
Wrap in aluminum foil and heat in oven.

title: wilted salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Chop onion and toss together with lettuce.
Meanwhile, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Drain on paper towel.
Mix 1/2 cup vegetable oil with bacon drippings left in pan.
Add vinegar.
Heat and pour over lettuce and onion.
Serve immediately.

title: raw apple - walnut cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Then mix in other ingredients except apples and nuts.
Add apples and nuts to mixture which will be very stiff.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan, which has been greased and floured.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325°.
Cool and ice with frosting.

title: microwave cracker snacks
directions: Microwave butter until melted.
Add the celery salt, onion salt, garlic salt and paprika to the melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Add cheese and crackers and stir around until crackers are coated thoroughly.
Microwave for 2 minutes, stir well until butter mixture is absorbed by crackers.
Stores well in an airtight container.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Toast sesame seeds by swirling in a nonstick skillet until they smell nutty.

title: grilled herb chicken salad
directions: Rinse and pat chicken breasts dry, cut the chicken into chunks.
Spray a medium skillet with vegetable spray.
Over medium-high heat, place chicken in skillet and sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Cook until chicken is no longer pink.
In a large bowl, place romaine lettuce, olives and red onion.
In a small bowl or pitcher, mix dijon mustard, white wine vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and olive oil.
Pour mixture over salad and toss well.
Place tomato quarters around the inside edge of bowl.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 as a meal or 6 as a side salad.

title: green tomato dippers
directions: Using a paring knife, trim vine cores from tomatoes. Slice in rounds 1/4-inch thickness. Place in a large mixing bowl. Add dressing, salt, pepper and garlic powder. With a wooden spoon, toss lightly to cover each slice evenly. Chill 30 minutes. Mix cornmeal and flour in a shallow dish. Place vegetable oil in a heavy skillet over medium heat. Pour tomatoes in a strainer; rinse lightly with warm water and allow to drain. Coat each slice of tomato in cornmeal-flour mixture.

title: avocado and crab filling
directions: If using frozen crabmeat, thaw and drain.
In a medium bowl, use 2 forks to flake crabmeat.
Stir in smashed avocado, lemon juice, chives, yogurt, chili powder and salt.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of mixture into toast shells or crackers.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: no crust sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except whipped cream, in blender.Blend at medium speed until well mixed.
Pour into greased (or Pam sprayed) 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be served warm or cool with a dollop of Cool Whip or plain.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put all ingredients in a large pot. Cook on low, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with Mexican finely shredded cheese and Santitos tortillas chips.

title: fantabulous chocolate pie
directions: Mix well and press thinly in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Fry bacon; add onions, green pepper, celery and parsley.
Cook until vegetables are soft.
Add flour and stir until slightly brown.
Add tomatoes, salt and chili powder.
Cook slowly until thick.
Add rice and shrimp.
Heat for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: applesauce custard
directions: Heat applesauce; add yolks, sugar, salt, flour, vanilla and butter.
Beat
egg	whites	until
stiff;
put
on top and brown lightly.

title: witches' hats
directions: Attach chocolate kiss to chocolate bottom of each cookie with decorating icing.
Pipe decorating icing around base of chocolate kiss.
Makes 32 witches' hats.

title: crunchy oven-fried fish
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen, and cut into serving size pieces. Combine flour, salt and lemon-pepper in a shallow dish. Set aside. Beat egg white in a bowl until frothy. Combine bred crumbs, cornmeal, lemon peel and basil. Dip top of fish fillets into flour mixture, shaking off any excess. Dip into egg white.
Coat with bread crumb mixture.
Spray an unheated shallow baking pan with nonstick coating.
Place fillets in baking pan, coating side up, tucking under any thin edges of fish.
Bake in a 450° oven for 6 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: shoo-fly cupcakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine and salt.
Take out 1 cup for crumbs for top.
Add molasses, water and soda (mix liquid with soda and combine with dry ingredients).
Put in cupcake papers and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 20 cupcakes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together and add shredded zucchini.

title: hot cheese biscuits
directions: Cream the stick of margarine with the Old English cheese.
Add salt, red pepper and flour gradually.
When smooth, drop in small balls on greased cookie sheet.
Place in refrigerator or freezer for at least 3 hours or overnight.
Bake in 400° oven until slightly browned, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: veggie dip
directions: Blend all together until smooth.
Serve with a big bowl or tray of veggies, whatever's handy or in season.

title: baked beans
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine pork and beans, onion, green pepper, brown sugar, barbecue sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Top with bacon.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: This recipe is for two 9-inch pies.
Mix dry ingredients; add to sour cream in double boiler and cook.
Add small amount of hot mixture to beaten egg yolks and blend.
Add eggs to hot mixture and cook 10 minutes or until thick.
Add vanilla and raisins. Fill baked shells.
Top with meringue and bake until meringue turns a pretty tan.

title: googie's banana bread(yield: 2 loaves)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: chili
directions: In Dutch oven or kettle, brown beef. Drain well. Add onion, celery, garlic and green pepper. Cook until soft.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 hours. Correct seasoning to taste.
Simmer, covered, 1 more hour. Makes about 5 quarts.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and green pepper in oil, until done.
Add the rest of the ingredients, mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole, cover and bake in 350` oven for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple surprise dessert
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add the pineapple.
Add the pecans. Roll the graham crackers very fine.
Sprinkle half in bottom of 2 pans, each 8 x 8-inch.
Spread mixture over the crumbs.
Sprinkle rest of graham cracker crumbs on top. Store in the refrigerator overnight (not in the freezer).
Serves 8 to 10 nicely.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all.
Form patties.
Fry.
Serve with lettuce and tomato on toasted buns.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan and boil for 2 hours.

title: swedish minted meringue trees
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Dust with flour.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and salt until foamy, white and double in volume. Beat in sugar until it dissolves completely and meringue stands in firm peaks.
Stir in peppermint extract and food coloring.
Form into tiny tree shapes.
Sprinkle with decorating candies.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Melt jelly and mustard together over low heat.
Boil Little Smokies in water a few seconds; drain and add to jelly mix. Slowly let come to a boil.
Cool and refrigerate until time to serve.
Heat again and keep warm in fondue pot or chafing dish. (Best if made one or two days ahead of time.)

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix together and place in pie shells.
Refrigerate.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook hamburger until brown.
Drain fat.
Add Cheez Whiz and let it melt over hamburger.
Add the taco seasoning mix by stirring all the ingredients together.
Serve with nacho chips or tortilla chips.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except raisins together.
Add raisins. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Chopped walnuts may be added if desired.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: In a saucepan, heat cranberry juice cocktail to boiling. Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
In a bowl, beat cranberry sauce with electric mixer on high speed for 1 minute. Stir into gelatin mixture. Chill in refrigerator until thickened (about 2 hours).
Fold in whipped topping until mixture is thoroughly blended. Spoon into dessert dishes or 9-inch prepared pie shell or graham cracker crust. Chill until firm, at least 2 or 3 hours or overnight.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix oil and dry ingredients, eggs and berries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: broccoli and egg au gratin
directions: Trim off large leaves and tough ends of broccoli.
Wash and separate into spears.
Cook in a small amount of boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Arrange spears in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with eggs and cheese.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring, until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour sauce over broccoli mixture. Melt margarine in saucepan and stir in breadcrumbs.
Brown lightly and sprinkle over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: zucchini pilaf
directions: Saute zucchini in the oil and garlic.
Remove from the pan. Add the rice and brown in butter.
Place the rice in a saucepan. Add the soup stock and white wine.
Bring to a boil without the lid.
Add salt.
Place the zucchini on the top of the rice.
Do not stir.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
Add the cheese when serving.

title: midwest bacon and cheese
directions: Makes enough canape spread for 24 Melba toast rounds or dry, crisp crackers.

title: pineapple-strawberry salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boiling point. Add and dissolve Jell-O. Let cool. Add Cool Whip and mix well. Add cottage cheese, pecans and strawberries. Refrigerate and congeal.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Place cupcake papers in muffin tins.
Place a vanilla wafer in each paper.
Mix all the other ingredients together except pie filling.
Pour into each cupcake paper.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
You can use any kind of pie filling to top cake after they are cooled.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil peeled and sliced carrots in salted water until soft; drain.
Mix cheese and butter with cooked carrots.
Pour in baking dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 300° until brown. It's a lot better than it sounds.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Cut corned beef and cheese into cubes.
Layer in a greased casserole (save some cheese for top).
Pour soup-milk mix over and add more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: chew cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mix well after each.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In large skillet or slow-cooking pot with browning unit, cook beef and onion until meat loses its red color.
Pour off excess fat.
In slow-cooking pot, combine beef and onion with tomato sauce, wine, oregano, garlic salt, basil, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.* Pour into greased shallow baking dish.
In the meantime, cook whole zucchini in a regular pan of boiling salted water about 15 minutes or until barely tender.
Cut lengthwise in halves and arrange, cut side up, on top of meat mixture in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: baked onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter and oil in covered saucepan for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and salt; cook over moderate heat until onions are transparent.
Add flour and stir for 3 minutes.
Raise heat and add broth and wine.
Season and simmer, partly covered, for 45 minutes.

title: aunt gayle's fruit pizza
directions: Cover a 14-inch pizza pan with foil. Slice cookies and place, overlapping, on pizza pan.
Freezing cookie dough will make it easier to slice.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Remove foil.

title: palacinka
directions: Add more flour; sift it in, if batter is thin.

title: never fail pie pastry
directions: Mix together flour, Crisco and salt with a pastry cutter. Mix remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture. Mix thoroughly but do not overwork! This recipe makes 4 pie crusts or 2 double crusts. Divide dough into 4 balls. Roll out on floured board, being very sure not to overwork the dough because it will get tough. Balls may be frozen. Just allow thaw time and roll out as needed.
Can do ahead.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mash bananas and lemon juice until smooth.
Cream oil and honey together.
Add bananas.
Sift dry ingredients and mix in wheat germ.
Add to bananas and stir in nuts.
Turn into a greased pan; bake 45 minutes.

title: quick strawberry pie
directions: Wash the strawberries and cut into slices.
Put the slices in a bowl; put the glaze into bowl and mix.
Pour the mixture into crust; cover evenly.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Chill 30 minutes. Ready to serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and shape in a ball.
Roll in chopped pecan pieces.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.

title: daddy's favorite gumbo
directions: Rub generous amounts of salt, garlic powder, Cayenne pepper on chicken and let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
In frying pan, cook smoked sausage until brown.
Drain and set aside. In medium bowl, combine onion, bell pepper and celery.
Set aside. Combine flour, 1/2 tsp. salt, 1/2 tsp. garlic powder and 1/2 tsp. Cayenne pepper. Coat chicken well in flour mixture.
Reserve 1/2 cup flour mixture.
In large cast iron skillet (no other type will work) heat 1 1/2 inches of cooking oil and fry chicken until brown on both sides. Drain.
Pour hot oil into glass measure cup, leaving brown particles in skillet.
Return 1/2 cup hot oil to pan.
Place skillet over high flame.
Use metal whisk and gradually stir in 1/2 cup flour mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until roux is dark red brown, about 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vegetable mixture until vegetables are soft.
Place stock in large Dutch oven and bring to a rolling boil. Add roux to stock by spoonfuls, stirring until each spoonful is dissolved.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Bone and dice chicken.
Add sausage, minced garlic and chicken.
Continue simmering for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: how to be a great friend
directions: This recipe will make you a great friend.

title: quick poppy seed loaf
directions: Combine first five ingredients in large mixing bowl. Beat well.
Stir in pecans and poppy seed.

title: holiday applesauce cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.

Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs to mixture, singly beating after each egg. Sift flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice and cloves together and add to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce, mixing after each addition. Blend in raisins and nuts.
Bake in wax paper lined layer pans. Grease sides and bottoms of pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat the cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours until set. Top with cherry filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: poppy seed nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, poppy seeds and baking powder.
In another bowl, beat eggs with milk, oil and vanilla until blended.
Stir liquids into dry ingredients until smooth.
Mix in the nuts.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes or until loaves test done.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove from pans. Finish cooling on racks.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: basic hot chocolate mix
directions: You can use sugar substitute if desired.
For a richer tasting mix, add 1/3 cup powdered nondairy coffee creamer and/or a tablespoon or so of malted milk powder.

title: vegetarian minestrone soup(8 servings)
directions: Thaw bread dough and let rise once.
Divide dough into 4 round loaves, about 4-inches in diameter.
Place on baking sheet coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool loaves on wire rack.
Slice top third of each loaf.
To make bread bowls, remove bread inside each loaf, leaving about 1/3-inch shell.
Reserve shells and tops.
Save inside of bread for breadcrumbs.

title: party dip
directions: With electric mixer, gradually blend soup into cheese; beat just until smooth.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups of dip.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Line 11 x 17-inch pan with graham cracker squares.
Mix margarine, egg, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, coconut and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread this mixture over crackers.
Add layer of crackers on top of this.
Put vanilla icing on top.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Trim crust from bread and cut each slice into 5 strips.
Place in oven, 200°, for 2 hours to make crisp.
Combine peanut butter and cooking oil in saucepan, stirring constantly, until smooth. Dip bread slices in this mixture.
Combine graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar; dip bread sticks into this mix after dipping in peanut butter and oil mix.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt almond bark; stir in peanut butter.
Add Cap'n Crunch cereal and nuts.
Stir well.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls. Allow to harden.

title: grandma's red potato salad
directions: Skin potatoes and boil whole until soft (stick a fork through easily).
Drain potatoes and cool enough to handle.
Slice potatoes into large bowl.
Add mayonnaise for desired consistency. Add chopped onions and celery (again only add enough to your taste).
Mix well; add chopped eggs, salt and pepper.
Again mix well.
Top with paprika and egg wedges for decoration. Refrigerate and serve.

title: special potato soup
directions: Saute celery & onion in butter in a large dutch oven until tender. Add next 9 ingredients; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat and mash vegetables with a potato masher. Add milk & cheese. Cook on low heat stirring consistently until cheese is melted. Makes 10 cups.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Mix in chopped vegetables.
Mix together the remaining ingredients in small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.
Keeps well.

title: monkey bread
directions: Separate biscuits and tear into bite-size pieces. Melt margarine.
Dip pieces into margarine, then into cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook bacon.
Cook onion in bacon drippings.
Add cabbage (cut in quarters), salt, pepper and water.
Cook on low for 10 minutes. Add vinegar and brown sugar.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes more.
Add crumbled bacon.
You may add a tart sliced apple the last 15 minutes if desired.

title: seafood soup
directions: Mix together and heat.
Do not boil.

title: broccoli-rice bake
directions: Saute celery, margarine and onion.
Melt milk and mushroom soup over low heat.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Add everything together. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cover with foil.

title: larri jean's vodka voo-doo punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; serve over ice.
Yield: 35 punch cups.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with dash of salt and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold in coconut.

title: huguenot torte
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs until frothy and lemon-colored.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in apples, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put mixture in a buttered 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until crusty and brown on top.
Serve with vanilla ice cream. Serves 6.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion in shortening until golden.
Add crumbs and parsley, mixing thoroughly.
Add oysters, seasonings, and eggs.
Add small amount of stock if oyster liquid does not moisten stuffing enough.
Place in buttered casserole, cover and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fiesta beef pie
directions: In large skillet, saute onions, green pepper and garlic in oil until onion is tender-crisp.
Add beef and cook until meat is browned.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in ketchup and next 3 ingredients.
Heat to boiling.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook the mixed vegetables on the stove or in the microwave until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Place in a large bowl.
Add kidney beans, celery, onion and green pepper.
In a saucepan over medium heat, bring sugar, vinegar and cornstarch to a boil, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Refrigerate.

title: easy to make
directions: Pour pineapple juice into a saucepan.
Mix together flour, sugar, eggs and butter.
Add to pineapple juice.
Mix and cook until thick.
When cool, add pineapple chunks, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill and enjoy.

title: hot chocolate
directions: In a saucepan, combine water, chocolate, sugar and salt.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until chocolate melts.
Gradually stir in milk.
Heat just to boiling.
Do not boil.

title: molded pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add juice from drained pineapple.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Combine sour cream with mixture and beat with a mixer until light and fluffy. Fold in nuts and pineapple.
Pour into lightly oiled mold. Congeal.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground meat, onion, peppers, salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cheese and heat until cheese has melted.
Serve with chips.

title: microwave creamy fudge
directions: Set your microwave on 50% power.
Combine sugar, butter, milk, marshmallows, cornstarch, and salt in 4 quart mixing bowl. Cook until it boils. (I stir every 2 or 3 minutes),
When it starts to boil, time it for 3 minutes, stirring after 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove the bowl from the oven and add the chocolate chips.
When they are pretty well melted, add the vanilla and nuts.
Use an 8 x 8 inch pan or the small glass utility pan.
Line with foil, leaving it stick up around the edges.
Pour in the fudge.
Put in freezer for 1 hour.
Lift the fudge out with the foil, peel off the foil and cut the fudge.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: hot dip
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend for one minute.
Put in medium saucepan.
Cook on low for 15 minutes.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate marshmallow peppermint dessert
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and chocolate.
Mix well. Cover 9 x 13-inch pan with 2/3 of crushed wafers.
Pour chocolate mixture over crumbs.
Combine Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Pour over chocolate.
Top with candy and remaining crumbs.
Chill 24 hours.

title: homemade french fries
directions: Preheat deep fryer on medium with the vegetable oil, add onion salt to the oil.
Cut potatoes into quarters.
Deep fry for 1 1/2 minutes, check, stir occasionally.
Remove when brown.
Place on paper toweling to drain.
Add salt as desired.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in bowl. Do not stir! Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Add vanilla. Beat for 2 minutes or until thick.
Pour into buttered 8-inch dish. Cool and cut into squares.

title: lumpia
directions: Roll and deep fry.

title: chocolate chip kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar to egg whites
while beating.
Beat until stiff, but not dry peaks form. Fold in chocolate.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and place in preheated 350°
oven.
Turn off heat. Leave for at least 3 hours.
Makes 60 small kisses.
Store in airtight container.

title: that pasta stuff
directions: Cook pasta according to pkg. directions. Mix pasta, chicken, peppers, onions, and olives. Pour Italian dressing over mixture and refrigerate until chilled. Before serving, sprinkle with feta cheese.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tenderloin casserole
directions: Roll tenderloin in flour; brown in oil with onion, celery and garlic.
Add soup and water with rice and pour all into casserole; cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Place batter into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: julie's kielbasa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate 1 hour or more (baste with marinade).
Kielbasi and/or links should be cooked (in marinade) according to package directions.

title: chicken divine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cooked, drained broccoli in the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place layer of cut up chicken over this.
Mix lemon juice, sour cream, mayonnaise and soups.
Spoon over chicken layer then sprinkle cheese on top.
You may top with buttered bread crumbs, crushed chips or Ritz crackers, crushed.
Refrigerate at this point.
Allow to come to room temperature and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: julia's moist chocolate chocolate cake
directions: Add dry ingredients together; mix.
Add wet ingredients to dry.
Use electric mixer; mix well.
Add chocolate chips last, by hand.

title: aunt rosey's mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef mixed with salt, pepper and cumin.
Add ingredients in layers.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes in 13 x 15-inch casserole sprayed with Pam.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown ground chuck in small amount of favorite shortening and break up into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour or until thick.
Serve hot on your favorite bun.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 700° until the timer dings.
This is real tasty and I had it for my 4th birthday.

title: trout almondine
directions: Put fillets in shallow pan and add milk to cover.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Put almonds with peel in small bowl; cover with water.
Place in microwave on High for 1 minute.
This will make peeling come off easily.
Sliver the almonds with paring knife and set aside.
Remove fillets from milk and put in flour mixture (flour, salt and pepper).
Toss lightly and shake off excess. Brown fillets in oil until lightly brown on both sides.
Discard oil.
Put butter in skillet and add nuts.
Saute until golden brown.
Place fillets on platter and covered with toasted almonds. Serve.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, add strawberries, breaking with fork as you stir.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill until set.

title: barley hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with one onion.
Cut up celery.
Soak barley in water; drain.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: texas toffee
directions: Line pan with foil. Place crackers flat on bottom of pan. Boil butter and sugar 3 minutes. Spread over crackers. Bake in 400° oven for 5 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over this while hot. Return to oven to melt. Remove and spread evenly. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Break into pieces when cool.

title: cherry bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix together the flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: stir and store bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over bran cereal.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Cover and keep refrigerated up to six weeks.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix corn bread, celery, onion and seasoning.
Add well beaten egg and butter; mix thoroughly.
Moisten with hot chicken broth until soft.
Pour into a well-greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or use to stuff a small chicken or turkey.

title: pinwheel snacks
directions: Let cheese reach room temperature.
Then, thinly spread cheese on slice of meat.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Tray freeze.
When frozen, slice 3/4 to 1-inch pieces.
Place on party dish with toothpicks on the side or freeze and use at a later date.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry; set aside. Layer broccoli, chicken, soup mixture, cheese and crumbs and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dad's bread pudding
directions: Heat milk until just under boiling.
Add sugar and salt.
Set aside to cool.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add vanilla.
Cut bread into cubes and spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix milk and egg mixture.
Pour over bread.
Sprinkle cinnamon and raisins over top.
Place pan in larger pan with 1/2-inch of water in it.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes (until knife inserted in center comes out clean).
Serves 6.

title: tired grandma cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir lightly.
Place in sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 475° for 45 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: "arni tis tihis" - lamb surprise
directions: Cube meat from leg of lamb in 4 to 5-inch pieces.
Place 1 cube of meat on a large square of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Add 1-inch cube of cheese, 1 small carrot, 1 small onion, 1 piece of celery, 1 medium potato, which has been pared and cut in half and rubbed with butter.
Add a squeeze of lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Fold the foil and refold tightly.
Bake 2 hours in 350° oven.
Serve each foil package intact on dinner plate, allowing each guest to open his own.

title: snickers bars
directions: First Layer:
Melt together 1/4 cup chocolate chips, 1/4 cup butterscotch chips and 1/4 cup peanut butter.
Microwave about 1 minute.
Mix well.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fried okra
directions: Select young tender pods of okra.
Wash, cut off ends and slice crosswise.
Mix salt, pepper, meal and flour in a bag or bowl.
Add okra and shake or stir until okra is covered with dry mixture.
Have the shortening hot in a skillet.
Add the okra. Cook until tender and browned, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and make into meatballs.
Brown in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Saute remaining ingredients for sauce.
Cook until well blended; thicken.
Add meatballs.
Simmer until well blended.
Serve with toothpicks or over rice.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Make up to 3/4 cup with cold water.
Refrigerate until almost set.

title: south of the border spinach dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Butter a 1-quart baking dish. Combine all ingredients. Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips or toasted pita bread. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: enchiladas
directions: Combine onion and water in a 1 1/2-quart covered casserole dish and microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Add crumbled ground beef. Microwave 2 1/2 minutes.
Drain and add cheese, sour cream, parsley, salt and pepper; set aside.
Wrap tortillas in paper towel and microwave 1 minute.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour half of this sauce into a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Place 2 1/2 tablespoons of meat mixture in center of each tortilla and roll up.
Place seam side down in the sauce.
Top with remaining sauce. Cover with plastic wrap.
Heat 11 to 12 minutes.
Turn after 5 1/2 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crescent cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until onion is transparent; drain. Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper. Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Top with cheese, then top with other pie crust.
Brush top with beaten egg and cut slits in top crust.
Bake according to pie crust directions (until crust is brown).

title: penny's kugel (noodle pudding)(served hot, as sweet vegetable, or dessert)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Beat eggs; add rest of ingredients (room temperature).
Mix together and add noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into large rectangular pan or glass casserole, either greased or sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and pour over other ingredients.
Chop all remaining ingredients into small pieces, with bacon fried crispy and cut into small pieces.
Mix in last 3 ingredients into salad bowl.
Serve and eat.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix and form into 1-inch balls.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 minutes.
Can be frozen and baked as directed when needed.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening in.
Add the yeast and buttermilk.
Mix with large spoon real good.
This makes a large bowl full.
Pinch off each day just the amount you want to bake.
This keeps a week to 10 days.
Keep remainder of dough in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Do not add any milk to mash.
Add 1/2 stick margarine or butter and Velveeta.
Beat until melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook noodles.
Saute onion and 1 stick margarine.
Put 1/2 onion mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch lasagna pan.
Add 3 noodles, 1/2 potato mixture, 3 more noodles, rest of potatoes, last 3 noodles, rest of the margarine and onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pork chops and apple casserole
directions: In large skillet brown chops slowly on both sides without added fat.
Remove chops and pour off fat.
Put apples in a shallow baking dish and distribute onion evenly over the top, overlapping if necessary.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover tightly with lid or tinfoil and bake in preheated 400° oven 45 minutes.

title: evelyn's famous tangy green beans
directions: Cook green beans in water; drain and keep warm.
Don't overcook as the beans will become mushy.
Combine mustard, sugar, butter, salt and pepper in a small pan.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until the butter melts.
Stir in the lemon juice and vinegar.
Pour over hot green beans.
Can be prepared ahead, adding the sauce to the beans just before serving.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and seasoning.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter and season to taste. Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl.
Shape dough into balls about the size of a small pecan.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes or until lightly golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Mix all ingredients until moist.
Stir vigorously for 30 seconds.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain.
Crumble meat over bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Slice onion on top of meat.
Add chicken soup (undiluted) and spread over onions, then put on a layer of Tater Tots.
Add the diluted cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix butter and sugar well with mixer.
Add eggs, salt, soda and vanilla.
Mix
well.
Add buttermilk and flour.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel
potatoes.
Cut
into thin slices.
Brown potatoes in hot oil.
Turn
heat to low.
Dot with butter and sprinkle sugar on top.
Cover with lid and turn off heat.
Let set for 10 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients and add Raisin Bran.
Allow to chill for 24 hours.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can add more raisins, if desired.
Makes large batch.
Batter will keep 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: holiday macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let stand 5 minutes.
Then drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to cool on wire racks right away or they'll stick!
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: burgundy stew
directions: Combine meat, carrots, celery and onions.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and basil; stir into meat mixture.
Stir in tomatoes and wine.
Cover tightly and bake at 300° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Sir in mushrooms and water chestnuts; cook 10 minutes longer.

title: beef burger casserole
directions: Place layers in a greased shallow pan.
Put ground beef on layers.
Add tomato soup and then mushroom soup.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
(Cheese may be added.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and cream cheese together.
Add confectioners sugar; mix well.
Beat in Cool Whip with electric mixer on low speed.
Pour into crust.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.

title: alicia's punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar in a 1 gallon container.
Add 8 cups water, stirring until well mixed.
Pour in pineapple juice.
Add enough water to fill container.
Yields 25 servings.

title: rabbit
directions: Brown rabbit with garlic in bacon drippings.
When brown, add other ingredients.
Cover tightly and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until rabbit is tender.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and soda.
Cut in softened margarine.
Add buttermilk and shape into large ball. Knead 6 to 8 times on lightly floured surface.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, or two 9-inch or three 8-inch round layer pans.
Beat all ingredients in a large mixing bowl at low speed for 30 seconds, scraping the bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes, scraping the bowl occasionally.
Pour into pans.
Bake until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean (about 45 to 50 minutes for oblong, 35 to 40 minutes for layers).
Cool.
Frost with Vanilla Butter Frosting, if desired.

title: bean salad
directions: Put in bowl.
Mix and pour over:

title: yummy egg noodles(fun to make!)
directions: Beat egg and add milk and salt.
Add flour until mixture is stiff.
Roll mixture on pastry cloth (well floured) and let sit for approximately 20 minutes.
Fold pastry in half and cut into strips.
Leave strips long enough to make them fun to eat!
Use immediately or refrigerate until ready to use!

title: marinade sauce
directions: Good marinade for pork chops.
After standing in sauce overnight, broil or charcoal grill chops.

title: basic pastry puffs
directions: Mix the water, butter and salt in a medium saucepan.
Heat just to boiling.
Immediately remove from heat and add the flour all at once.
Stir with a wooden spoon until mixture forms a ball. Return to medium heat and cook, stirring constantly until paste has dried slightly.
Remove from heat and let cool for 5 minutes. Beat in eggs one at a time, waiting until each is incorporated before adding another.
When each egg is added and you start to beat it in, the mixture separates slightly and look like Southern dumplings.
Continue beating until the mixture looks like mashed potatoes. Do this with each egg.

title: pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl; beat until smooth.
Drop onto hot griddle or frying pan.
Serve with maple syrup or jelly, hot coffee or tea.

title: pizza quiche
directions: Brush pie shell with Worcestershire sauce.
Add cheese, mushrooms, pepperoni, ham and olives, etc.
Beat eggs, cream and hot sauce; pour over other ingredients.
Top with onions rings, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover bottom of pan with coconut and nuts.
Pour cake mixture on top.
Mix margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar, and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Spoon in globs on top of cake mix.
Bake at 325° about 40 minutes.

title: krafty-cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and reserve 1/4 cup drippings. Crumble bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Microwave beans as directed on package.
Drain well.
Add mushrooms and onion to reserved 1/4 cup drippings in large skillet.
Cook on medium-high heat for 10 minutes; drain.
Add bacon, hot green beans and pepper.
Mix lightly.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Have a baked pie shell ready.
Mix the water, sugar, cornstarch and jello in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Put stemmed berries in pie shell and pour mixture over all.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: dill dip for raw vegetables
directions: Combine ingredients in order given and mix well.
Good as vegetable or chip dip.

title: cincinnati pie
directions: Combine ground beef, potato, peas, corn, cauliflower, carrots and onion in a large cast-iron skillet.
Add mushroom soup, spreading evenly over vegetables-beef mixture.
Pour batter over all to create topping.
Place skillet in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
Test corned beef topping with a toothpick for doneness.
Remove skillet from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix together the sugar, cocoa, salt and milk in a glass bowl; top with 1/2 cup butter.
Cook on High in 9 x 9-inch glass dish for 3 minutes.
Stir well.
Mix in nuts or leave plain.
Refrigerate. Cut after 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stuff
directions: Mix ground chuck, onion, garlic, salsa, salt and pepper. Cook until onions and garlic are tender. Layer meat mixture and flour tortillas until all are used. Sprinkle small amount of cheese between each layer. End with meat mixture. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: christmas cole slaw
directions: Mix, cover and chill several hours.

title: coffee walnut chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 12 (3-inch) muffin pans cups (or use paper cups).
Cream the butter with the sugars, coffee and vanilla. Beat together the eggs and milk. Combine the flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternately add the wet and dry ingredients to the butter mixture. Stir just to combine (use wooden spoon). Add chips and walnuts.
Fill the tins full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes (depending on your oven). Cool 5 minutes, then remove and cool on racks.
Beat eaten soon after baking, but can be warmed in oven or toaster.

title: creamiest banana puddin'
directions: Mix 2 boxes of vanilla pudding and milk.
Mix 1 cup at a time until all 5 are blended.
Let set for a few minutes.
Add Cool Whip to pudding mixture.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese and condensed milk.
Add to pudding mixture.
Layer cookies on bottom and sides of pan.
Pour in some of the pudding mixture.
Add a layer of sliced bananas.
Repeat layers several times.

title: jeannette's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with 3/4 cup crushed potato chips and 2 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients until the cheese becomes stringy. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole or pan at 350° for 45 minutes or a little longer.

title: glaze for ham
directions: Melt all together and baste over grilled or baked ham.

title: opie's lemonade pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine the Cool Whip, lemonade and milk, blending well.
Pour in graham cracker crust and chill for 2 hours.

title: caramelized grahams
directions: On foil lay graham crackers.
Boil in sauce pan butter and brown sugar.
Pour on 100% of crackers and cover with foil and cook in oven for 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix meat, oats, chopped tomatoes and chilies, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Then, if necessary, drain grease from pan.
Pour tomato sauce over the top of meat loaf and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt; stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour in greased dish; refrigerate for 2 hours or 24.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oriental chicken(microwave)
directions: Pierce chicken breasts with a fork.
Arrange in a 3-quart casserole.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover.
Microwave on High (power 10) for 11 to 13 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add 1 egg at a time. Add sifted flour, salt and blend in chocolate syrup, flavoring and black walnuts. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Make icing and pour over cake while hot.

title: millet loaf
directions: Brown millet and onion in oil (or may omit this step and add to rest of ingredients without oil).
Add enough water to tomatoes and soup to make total of 4 cups.
Mix all ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May top with Cheddar cheese if desired.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add boiling water gradually while stirring constantly.
Boil 6 minutes, then remove from heat. Add butter, lemon juice, salt and nutmeg.
Serves 6.
Serve with bread, steamed or cottage pudding.

title: banana nut bread(ada recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream together margarine and sugar.

Add eggs; beat well. Add dry ingredients alternately with banana, mixing well. Stir in nuts. Pour into 3 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans, sprayed with vegetable Pam spray. Bake 40 to 50 minutes until toothpick comes out clean. (Freezes well.) Remove from pan. Cool on rack. Makes 17 slices (1/2 inch) per pan. Each contains 132 calories.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Place cubed potatoes (leave peeling on) in bowl.
Pour oil over potatoes.
Add dressing mix and toss well.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: scorned woman buffalo wings
directions: Deep fry wings at 400° (high) for 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy, then drain.
Pour melted butter or margarine over wings in a large bowl or pan, coating them.
Then pour the hot sauce over the wings, again thoroughly coating the wings.
(If cooking a larger amount or using a smaller deep fryer, cooked wings may be kept warm in oven at low temperature until others are ready.)
Finally, sit back.
Enjoy and have a fire extinguisher nearby, if desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 can onions, and mix well. Pour into dish.
Sprinkle reserved onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump cobbler
directions: Pour cans of filling or fruit cocktail in bottom of Dutch oven. Sprinkle cake mix over top of fruit, DO NOT STIR!
Sprinkle with cinnamon and cut pads of butter and let fall on surface.
DO NOT STIR, it will burn.
Cover and bake until bubbly and top is lightly browned, about 30-45 minutes.
Any combination of fruits can be used.
I recommend 1 can apple filling and 1 can of fruit cocktail.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add celery and saute 10 minutes. Add rest of ingredients except peppers and simmer for about 40 minutes.
Add green peppers and cook about 10 minutes longer. Serve with Parmesan cheese and Italian bread or over pasta.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix butter, eggs and beer.
Add to dry ingredients.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and crush smooth.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be served at room temperature or hot with your favorite wheat crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Combine corn, rice, pimientos, pepper, sugar, salt and pepper.
Beat in egg; pour in casserole dish. Butter; top with grated cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees; use a 10 inch bundt pan.
Cream butter, in small mixer bowl until thick and lemon colored.	Blend into creamed mixture.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.

Stir in 1 teaspoon coconut, rum, butter, vanilla and lemon flavorings.	Spoon into greased and floured bundt pan.	Bake for 1-1/2 hours or until cake tests done. Bring remaining flavorings, 1 cup sugar 1/2 cup water to a boil in saucepan; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour half the mixture over cake in pan.
Cool for several minutes, invert cake onto cake plate.
Pour remaining glaze over top.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Add spices and mushrooms.
Spread on party bread slices.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Watch time.
Mixture may be frozen.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half, scoop out seeds and spread butter over cut wedges.
Place cut side down in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Turn cut side up; brush with lemon juice.
Place 1 teaspoon butter in each cavity. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon brown sugar over each acorn squash half; sprinkle with coriander.
Return to oven and bake about 5 minutes or until sugar has melted.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Combine mustard and jelly.
Add wieners.
Cook in crock-pot for 2 hours.
Serve hot.

title: autumn apple loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nuts. In a large bowl, beat margarine or butter, sugar and 1 egg until smooth. Add second egg and beat well. Stir in vanilla. Stir in apples. Pour flour mixture into batter. Stir until moistened. Scrape into a loaf pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: butterscotch walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add corn syrup, salt, vanilla, brown sugar and butter; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 35 minutes or until filling sets in 375° oven.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Combine ingredients and dip seasoned shrimp in batter. Fry until brown.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Mix vinegar with milk and allow to curdle.
Add onion, garlic, parsley, mayonnaise, Blue cheese, lemon juice, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: sale creek strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil and strain 1 cup of the smallest berries, the sugar and the boiling water.
Now add the cornstarch mixture. Cook over the fire for a couple of minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from fire and beat.
Return to a slow fire and cook slowly until thick.
Have ready a baked pie shell.
Arrange the rest of the berries, which have been washed and picked over, in the pie shell.
Pour the hot sauce over them.
When cool, spread with whipped cream that has been sweetened with powdered sugar.

title: chex-muddy buddies(kids')
directions: Pour cereals into large bowl and set aside.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in 1-quart microwave bowl. Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl. Mix until smooth and creamy. Add chips and flour. Mix well. Form into small balls and place on an ungreased baking sheet. Press flat with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake in a preheated 350° oven 16 to 18 minutes.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Sprinkle steak with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Cook steak and garlic in butter until meat is brown.
Add onions and green peppers; continue cooking until vegetables are wilted.
Add tomatoes and broth; cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Blend water with cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir into steak and cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: carne asada
directions: Pierce steak with fork on both sides and coat with oil.
Place in large resealable plastic bag.
In measuring cup, combine Fajitas Skillet Sauce, orange juice and oregano.
Pour over steak.
Marinate in refrigerator, 1 to 2 hours, turning steak occasionally.
Remove steak; reserve marinade.
Broil steak 4 to 5 minutes on each side, until cooked to desired doneness, basting often with reserved marinade.
Serve with salsa.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup.
Shape into patties.
Chill or freeze overnight.
Remove from refrigerator.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet (in Crisco or oil).
Put in shallow pan.
Cover with soup.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: irish tater candy
directions: Peel and boil potato, when done, mash up with fork.
Add pinch of salt and pour in a box of confectioners sugar.
This makes a stiff dough.
Roll out on a dough board that has been floured real good in a layer 1/4-inch thick.
Spread peanut butter all over top. Roll up like a jelly roll.
Makes 2 rolls if you like.
Put in the refrigerator and chill.
Cut with knife and serve.

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 the cheese with all other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and sprinkle 1/2 the cheese on top.
Remove from oven when cheese is melted.
Cut into squares and serve warm.

title: stir-fry vegies
directions: Scrub potatoes well and place on oven rack.
Bake at 375° about an hour to hour and a half (depends on size of potatoes).
Potatoes should feel soft when squeezed with pot holder.
Store the ones you are not using right away in plastic wrap in the refrigerator.
They will keep at least a week.
Heat in microwave and eat.

title: chinese peas
directions: Heat oils, then put in vegetables and cook about 15 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Dissolve 1/4 cup of broth and cornstarch, then add remaining broth and soy sauce; cook until thick.
Pour over vegetables and heat.
Serves 10.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and oleo.
Place in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Cool.
Cream the sugar and cheese together; spread Cool Whip over cooled pretzels.
Spread cheese mixture over Cool Whip.
Combine boiling pineapple juice and water with strawberry Jell-O; cool. Add pineapple and strawberries to Jell-O.
Chill and pour over layers.

title: snacks
directions: Cut apples into quarters.
Put 1 spoonful of peanut butter in center.
Add raisins and eat.

title: butterfinger brownies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In medium bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, combine margarine and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture and 1 cup crushed Butterfinger candy bars.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining crushed candy bars over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes approximately 20 bars.

title: raisin-nut whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add salt, oil and molasses. Stir well.
Add wheat germ, flours, nuts and raisins.
Use about 1 cup of white flour in kneading.
Flour varies, so use enough flour to make a proper dough.
Knead well.
Set aside to rise until double in bulk.
Knead again and form into 6 loaves.
Let rise again in loaf pans.

title: harker's island clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon in bottom of stew pot until crisp.
Crumble bacon and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring often until potatoes are tender.

title: fruited cream cheese spread
directions: Mash fruits until desired consistency and then blend in cream cheese.
Keep cold.
Serve with bagels, gingersnaps, etc.
Yields 2 cups.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead about 1 minute.
Shape dough into 12 balls.
Place in an 8-inch square pan coated with cooking spray.
Flatten dough slightly.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Makes 12 biscuits.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and put aside.
In a large bowl, combine rest of ingredients.
Then add rice. Put in casserole dish and bake in oven at 375° to 400° for 15 minutes.

title: make ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch dish. Crumble sausage and cook until browned.
Drain drippings and spread over croutons.
Whisk eggs and milk.
Stir in soup, spinach, mushrooms, cheeses and mustard.
Pour egg mixture over sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake 50 to 55 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Yield 10 to 12 servings.

title: western bean dish
directions: Fry bacon crisp, put aside.
Brown hamburg with onion in a large skillet.
Drain off.
Combine all remaining ingredients. (Be sure to drain all liquid from beans.)
Put in casserole.
Heat in oven until hot through and through.
Sprinkle bacon over and serve.

title: cholesterol-free apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend together cake mix, pie filling and egg whites in a large mixer bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes on medium speed.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Spread half of the batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of sugar and cinnamon over batter.
Repeat with remaining batter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 20 to 35 minutes, until wooden toothpick, inserted in center, comes out clean.
Cool.

title: whole wheat dinner rolls
directions: In small saucepan, heat first 3 ingredients until very warm (120° to 130°).
In large bowl, blend warm liquid, 1 cup all-purpose flour, 3/4 cup whole wheat flour, sugar, salt, yeast and egg at low speed until moistened.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining wheat flour and enough all-purpose flour to form stiff dough.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Place dough in vegetable-sprayed bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size, 45 to 60 minutes.
Then punch down dough. Divide dough in 20 pieces; shape into balls.
Place on greased pan; cover and let rise for 30 to 45 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Slice two eggs into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In saucepan, melt margarine and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir sausage and corn into sauce and pour over eggs.
Slice remaining eggs; arrange on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: *Milk and cheese can be substituted with low-fat variety.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and tomato; mash together, leaving small lumps. Add all other ingredients. Mix well with hand. Add salt and stir with a spoon. Serve cold with taco Doritos.

title: peanut butter banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in a heavy saucepot; add eggs and milk, mixing well. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly 25 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: easy so easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 9-inch tube pan; line with wax paper and grease again (or use generously greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan).
Sift together flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend in dry ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan; remove wax paper.
Glaze and garnish as desired.

title: carrot, sweet potato and apple tzimmes
directions: Cook the carrots and sweet potatoes until tender; drain.
Pare, quarter, core and slice the apples, but not too thin.
Alternate these in layers in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Season each with brown sugar, salt, pepper and fat.
Add water.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until apples are tender. Remove cover and continue baking until top is golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: fritata
directions: Drain juice from one artichoke jar into frying pan.
Chop both jars of artichokes and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in frying pan of marinade.
Beat eggs.
Add bread crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and Tabasco.
Stir in cheese, parsley and artichokes.
Add onion mixture.
Put in 7 x 11-inch greased pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats.
Cream shortening and add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add flour.
Fold in oats with dates and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.

title: spinach omelet
directions: Cook and drain chopped spinach.
Put 2 slices of bread in bottom of buttered loaf pan.
Top with layer of spinach and cheese. Repeat, having cheese on top.
Beat eggs; add milk and seasoning and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Heat butter until melted; add garlic.
Stir in flour and salt and cook until bubbly.
Stir in milk and broth and boil one minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in 1/2 cup Parmesan, Mozzarella, onion, basil, oregano and pepper until cheese melts.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables.
Drain.
Mix next four ingredients.
Stir in vegetables.
Moisten cracker crumbs with butter, put half in casserole.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Put remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: party dip
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Add Worcestershire sauce and spinach.
Mix well.
This needs to be made a day before or at least eight hours before serving.

title: delicious frozen cole slaw
directions: Boil 3 to 4 minutes and let cool.

title: rice pudding supreme(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine milk, pudding mix, rice and raisins in deep glass bowl (2-quart preferred).
Microwave 11 to 13 minutes or until mixture boils.
Stir once during last half of cooking time.
Cool.
Fold pudding, whipped cream and fruit together in large mixing bowl. Refrigerate until served.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook over low heat for about 45 minutes. Turn to moderate heat and bring to a boil; remove from heat immediately.
Add the Certo; stir well.
Put in jars.

title: pineapple cream cheese mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir in measured liquid.
Pour 2 cups of the gelatin into medium bowl.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in pineapple.
Spoon into 5-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate about 2 hours until set but not firm.
Stir remaining 1 cup gelatin gradually into cream cheese in small bowl until smooth.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in walnuts; spoon into mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm; unmold.

title: chocolate caramel treats
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Gradually beat in flour and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips; set aside 1 cup. Press remaining mixture into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are light brown.
In small heavy saucepan over low heat, melt caramel candies with milk.
Drizzle over base.
Sprinkle with reserved oat mixture. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes about 2 dozen squares.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add cream, melted butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus egg casserole
directions: Prepare asparagus and cut into 2-inch pieces.
Cook in 1-inch of boiling salted water until tender.
Make white sauce of butter, flour, seasonings and milk.
Stir in cheese.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch oblong pan or 2 round pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with banana, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts. Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan; cook on rack.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: hawaiian beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cut pineapple slices in half and saute in drippings until light brown.
Combine other ingredients in skillet.
Arrange pineapple on top.
Heat until bubbly.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions and peppers in olive oil until onions are soft. Do not brown them.
Pour in saucepan.
Add tomato sauce and water. Simmer on low heat.
Using the same skillet, brown beef and garlic.
Pour in pan with onions and other ingredients.
Add spices and salt to taste.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: finger appetizers
directions: Open canister of French loaf and unroll.
Layer with sliced pepperoni. Cover pepperoni with grated Mozzarella.
Re-roll. Pierce with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Slice into 1 inch strips.
Serve hot.

title: party cookies(sugar cookies)
directions: Cream
the
oleo
and sugar.
Stir in oil and egg.
Mix the rest
of
the
ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.	Shape 1/2-inch balls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Dip balls in green sugar and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: lebkuchen cookies
directions: Mix walnuts, fruit and orange peel. Combine flour, soda, spices and coffee.
Sprinkle over fruit and nut mixture.
Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg.
Add honey and sourdough starter alternately with flour and nut mixture.
Mix well. Spread on greased jelly roll pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes or until done. Remove from oven. Frost with rum glaze.
Cool. Cut into bars.
Yields 2 dozen cookies.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt shortening in heavy skillet.
Pour in rice and onion; brown over low heat, stirring frequently.
Add broth and tomatoes. Do not stir.
Cover and let steam over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: raisin and coconut pie
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add raisins, coconut, nuts and vinegar. Melt margarine and pour in mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Then cut oven back to 350° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: momma's peanut brittle
directions: You also need 1 buttered pan; have ready ahead of time.

title: tomato-cheese fondue
directions: Pour tomato juice over bread crumbs and let soak.
Stir in cheese, melted butter and salt.
Beat egg yolks and stir into bread crumb mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in thoroughly.
Turn into buttered 6 cup casserole and bake in moderate oven (325°) for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until a sharp knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, bring broth, soup and vegetables to a boil.
Stir well.
Add chicken and cook 10 minutes.
Pour mixture into baking dish and top with biscuits. Bake until biscuits are golden brown.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets and boil until fork-tender.
Peel and cut to desired size.
Boil vinegar, sugar, cloves and salt.
Add beets and reheat to boiling.
Pack into jars and cover with liquid. Seal.

title: baked beans and tomatoes
directions: Cook beans until done, then mix with cooked macaroni.
Add tomatoes and sugar.
Season with salt, pepper and butter.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water and cook to the soft ball stage.
Add peanuts and cook until mixture turns dark.
Remove from heat; add baking soda, salt and vinegar.
Stir well and pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: brownies
directions: Heat chocolate, oil and sugar on low.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Pour in greased pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: artichoke toast
directions: Cut crusts from bread.
Quarter bread slices.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Toast both sides under broiler.
Combine mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread lightly on toast pieces.
Cut artichokes in quarters.
Place on each toast piece.
Top with teaspoon of mayonnaise mixture.
Place under broiler until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: eggless, butterless and milkless cake
directions: Put ingredients in a pan and boil 3 minutes.
When cool, stir in 1 teaspoon soda, dissolved in a little hot water, then add 2 cups flour in which 1/2 teaspoon baking powder has been sifted.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix altogether and refrigerate.
Add more dressing and cheese if so desired.

title: sauteed chicken in red wine vinegar
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until very soft, 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Add chicken and cook until golden brown and juices run clear when pierced with tip of a knife.
Remove chicken.
Add vinegar and boil until reduced to 2/3, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add cream and boil until thickened, 3 to 4 minutes.
Return onion and
chicken to skillet and spoon sauce over.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Peel onion; set in same pan as the meat and roast until fairly tender.
Cut meat and onion up fine.
Boil potatoes and turnip; dice.
Mix with meat.
Add salt and pepper.
Roll out pastry fairly thin (1/4-inch).
Cut into rounds the size of a saucer.
Put meat mixture in the center of each round.
Bring 2 opposite sides of pastry together in a join at the top and flute edges.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake in hot 425° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
This mixture will make several dozen pasties.

title: imperial pound cake
directions: Scald 3 cups of milk in top of double boiler.
Mix 1 cup cold milk with cornmeal; pour cornmeal mixture slowly into hot milk. Place mixture over boiling water and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
