Add sugar, butter and molasses and remove from heat. Add salt and spices; stir in beaten eggs and pour into well buttered 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes during first hour.
After first hour, pour cream over top of pudding and continue to bake without stirring in cream.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: seven course casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in casserole dish.
Season each layer. Bake 2 to 3 hours in slow oven at 325° in covered dish.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.

title: dawn's meatloaf
directions: Break egg into bowl, beat slightly.
Add milk, salt, pepper and bread crumbs.
Beat until bread has blended in well.
Add onions, carrots, cheese and beef.
Mix well with hands.
Pack into a 9 x 5 inch loaf pan.
Combine brown sugar, catsup and mustard. Spread over surface of loaf.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Can freeze raw for baking later.

title: smoked ham
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Punch about 8 holes in top of can with can opener.
Put in oven about 15 to 20 minutes to melt gelatin around ham.
Pour off gelatin.
Pour liquid smoke into can.
Bake 3 hours at 250°.

title: homemade pot pie dough
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Add milk until dough is soft.
Divide into 4 to 6 batches.

Roll out paper thin, keeping your area well floured. Keep flipping your dough from top to bottom as you roll it out. Bring your broth to a boil and drop in your pot pie once it is cut into small, squared 1 x 1-inch or 2 x 2-inch pieces.
Boil 20 minutes; add meat and seasonings, such as parsley and onions.

title: 15 minute super sundae pie
directions: Spoon ice cream into crust.
Place in freezer with plastic lid inverted on top of ice cream.
Remove from freezer when hard. Spoon jar of strawberry topping onto pie.
Cut and place on plate. Garnish with chocolate syrup, whipped cream and cherry.

title: crab cakes
directions: Clean and pick over crabmeat, removing any membrane pieces. Combine the other ingredients together and add to crabmeat.
Mix gently until blended.
Form into 8 crab cakes.
Fry each in oil deep enough to come up to one half the side of the crab cake. Brown lightly on each side.

title: yummy yams
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat yams until smooth and add all other ingredients (except marshmallows and pineapple).
Blend until smooth.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into baking dish.
Layer small can of pineapple on top, slices, chunks or crushed will work.
Add rest of yam mixture.
Top with marshmallows and pecans.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Dredge roast in flour; brown in Dutch oven with a little oil. Add salt and pepper.
Add a little water (about 2 cups).
Cook 2 hours; watch so it doesn't dry out.
Add more water if needed. Add cut up carrots, onions and potatoes as desired.
A bay leaf or two may be added to roast if desired.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Put raw, cubed beef into a 3-quart casserole.
(Do not brown.) Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil. Top with celery, carrots, onions and potatoes. Combine tomato soup and water.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Do not stir, leave in layers.
Cover tightly and bake for 3 hours at 300°.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch; cook and stir until thick and clear.
Cool slightly; add vanilla.
In a large bowl beat egg whites and salt until droopy peaks form.
Continue beating as you slowly pour in the water and sugar mixture.
Beat until peaks stand up straight.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until well blended.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix and sift first 4 ingredients.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Stir in raisins. Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into dry mixture until just moistened.
Bake in 1-quart casserole (greased) at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and blend well. Add milk and juice; mix well.
Freeze in ice cream freezer following manufacturer's directions.

title: dill pickle surprise
directions: Rinse and cut in thick slices; put in 2 (1 gallon) jars.
Add 1/2 garlic to each jar.
Pour 1/3 cup oil over each jar.
Add 4 1/2 cups sugar to each jar and seal.
Shake until all sugar is dissolved.
I shake ever so often for about 2 hours and chill in refrigerator for about 3 days.
Delicious.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all together except the crackers.
Put crackers in a bowl and coat with the mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 250°.

title: squash puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients, then add enough water drained from squash for consistency to
drop with a teaspoon in deep fat to form puffs about the size of hush puppies.
Makes 20 to 25 puffs.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Make jello according to directions.
Mix in rest of ingredients and chill to set.

title: dump cake
directions: In a deep casserole dish, dump in peaches.
Then sprinkle the cake mix across the top to cover peaches.
Cut butter into small pieces and place it over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly and golden brown.

title: ham and cheese souffle
directions: Trim crusts off bread and butter both sides and then cube. Butter casserole dish.
Layer bread, ham and cheese, then layer another layer of bread, ham and cheese.
Pour beaten eggs and milk on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients but olive oil together in blender, then slowly add olive oil in steady stream while blending.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together including spaghetti which has been broken into pieces.
Place in a 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake another 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: linguini and chicken scampi
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2 pieces.
Dip in egg and bread crumbs seasoned with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add 1/3 of chicken and saute 30 seconds until golden. Remove with slotted spoon and repeat with remaining pieces. Discard oil.
Cook pasta.

title: la crepe francaise
directions: Place flour and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add salt and sugar; mix well.
When ingredients get too heavy to mix, add milk and mix well.
Add vanilla and melted butter; mix well.
Cover bowl; let stand for 1 hour.
Using heated skillet or pan, use a small amount of Crisco to grease pan.
When pan is hot (not too hot), spread pancake mix in pan and brown both sides (golden brown only). Serve with warm maple syrup.
Serves 4.

title: deluxe beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown ground beef, then drain excess grease off of meat.
Then take ground beef, margarine and tomato sauce.
Mix together.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green peppers in a bowl.
Spread half the drained noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and top with cheese mixture.
Add remaining noodles.
Spread meat and tomato mixture on top.
Cover with foil and bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: green chili pie
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and soup. Simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Using 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the following ingredients: put refried beans down first; tortilla chips second; meat mixture third and follow through with cheese. Repeat procedures ending with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cover with foil first 20 minutes to prevent cheese from burning.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak in bite size pieces, roll in flour and brown it.
Put in large pot and simmer meat in soup, onion and celery until meat is tender, about 2 hours.
After meat is tender, put mushrooms in.
About 30 minutes before you want to serve, add sour cream.
If you need more liquid, add more soup.
Serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: butter roll delicious
directions: Cream together butter with half cup sugar.
Mix together and bring to a boil: 1/2 cup milk, water, nutmeg and vanilla.
Make a dough out of flour, baking powder, salt, shortening and 1/2 cup milk.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Spread butter and sugar mixture over this, then roll dough as for jelly roll.
Cut into 1-inch rolls and place in large shallow greased baking dish.
Pour the syrup over this and bake at 375° until syrup thickens, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon before baking, if desired. Makes 12 servings.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook rice; drain, rinse and set aside to cool for at least 1 hour.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package.
Fold in pineapple, cherries and sugar.
Blend in rice and chill.

title: lit'l smokies corn wraps
directions: 1) Separate dough into 16 strips; cut each strip in half.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine Carnation milk with sugar in a saucepan.
Heat on medium heat to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into a buttered pan and cool.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and remove skin and bones. Place chicken in a long baking dish.
Add salt and pepper and dot with butter or margarine.
Save the chicken broth in which chicken was cooked.
Mix the cream of chicken soup, 1/4 cup of chicken broth and the milk.
Pour this over the chicken.
Saute the celery and onion in butter or margarine.
Add to this the Pepperidge Farm dressing, the beaten egg and 2 1/2 cups of the chicken broth. Spread this over the chicken and soup layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: salsa
directions: Process in blender for 10 seconds or desired consistency. Simmer 1 hour.
Cool, then store, covered in refrigerator.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: heavenly nut cake
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Bring to boil.
Then mix into remaining ingredients and blend together.
Pack into pan with stem that has been buttered well and refrigerate overnight.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine all dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add water, honey and flavoring into dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls and press with a fork.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam and place cookies on it.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Quickly saute the cooked ham in butter, cream, basil, salt and pepper.
Place the macaroni in a well oiled casserole dish.
Set ham on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs.
Place casserole in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients but oil until well blended.
Add oil and beat until smooth.
Pour onto hot waffle iron; cook until golden brown.

title: pinto-cornbread casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Put into large rectangle baking dish.
Layer the beans.
Layer the sauce.
Pour cornbread mix on top.
Bake until bread browns at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: microwave rice pilaf
directions: Place a marshmallow on top of half a graham cracker.
Microwave on High for 10 to 15 seconds.
Immediately top with half of a 1.5 ounce chocolate bar.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Slightly soften liverwurst and cream cheese.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Make a few days in advance.
Serve with party rye bread.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, beating together well.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating well after addition.
Add jam and beat.
Sift flour, salt and spices together.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add flour and milk alternately to cream mixture, beating after each addition.
Bake in greased and floured 9-inch tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Combine liquids.
Freeze some in a ring mold to keep punch cold.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion and chopped green pepper together; drain off grease.
Mix with beans, tomato sauce, ketchup, steak sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Put in a cake pan; sprinkle black pepper all over.
Prepare corn bread according to directions on the package; add sugar.
Pour batter evenly over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for about 1/2 hour or until cornbread is browned.

title: broccoli-bacon salad
directions: Cook and drain bacon.
Crumble; reserve 1/3 for salad top. Wash, drain and pat dry the broccoli.
Slice onion in thin rings. Combine broccoli, onion, 1/2 cup cheese (reserving 1/2 cup to put on top of salad), raisins and 2/3 of bacon bits.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and sugar to make dressing.
Mix dressing with other ingredients and marinate overnight.
When ready to serve, toss lightly and top with reserved cheese and bacon bits.

title: family's favorite salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake when serving.

title: bagel pizza
directions: Place bagels on baking sheet.
Spread with tomato sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (lightly), oregano, basil, garlic powder, pepper and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: margie's zucchini quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Mix all ingredients and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Enough for 2 pies.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough.
Scrub and wash.
Cut potatoes into the skin in thin slices but not all the way through. Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 450° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: banana split smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender except yogurt.
Cover and process until smooth.
Add yogurt.
Process until blended.
Serve immediately.

title: rice stew
directions: Mix all ingredients except oleo in a rice cooker.
Put oleo in pats over the top of mixture.
Cook according to rice cooker instructions.

title: t.v. mix
directions: Melt butter in a very large baking pan.
Pour rest of ingredients over butter and stir very well.
Bake 2 hours in 200° oven stirring every 20 minutes.

title: avocado salad
directions: Sprinkle avocado with 2 to 3 tablespoons lemon juice and salt; toss gently to coat.
Combine avocado, olives and celery; mix gently.
Combine mayonnaise and 1 tablespoons lemon juice; mix well.
Stir mayonnaise mixture into rest of mixture.
Serve salad on lettuce leaves; garnish with egg quarters and pimiento strips. Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Layer
corn
and crushed saltine crackers in a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with milk and put pats of butter across the top.
Bake until golden and not soggy.
Serve hot.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in bread crumbs.
In a 1-quart casserole, layer half the tomatoes; sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Cover with half the crumb mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: breaded pasta
directions: Heat oil in medium skillet.
Add garlic and saute.
Add bread crumbs and cook until browned.
Add pasta and stir.
Cook until hot.

title: skillet steak and rice
directions: Pound steak; cut into serving size pieces.
In skillet, brown steak in shortening and pour off fat.
Add soup, water, wine, onion and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add rice and Brussels sprouts, bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover.
Cook 10 minutes or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Mix
all
of
the ingredients, except sherbet together. Add 1 can
of
water for the pink lemonade and 1 can of water for
the orange
juice.
Make
an ice mold of fruit punch and raspberries. Add the sherbet just before serving.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook or heat vegetables, onion and beans, then drain.
Combine other ingredients and cook until clear.
Pour over vegetables. Let set for 8 hours.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Stir together first four ingredients.
Add melted butter; mix until crumbly.
Pat into an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cream together the cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar.
Add egg, lemon peel and lemon juice; mix well. Pour over baked layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with the 2 tablespoons graham crackers.
Cool; cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 36.

title: spiced tea
directions: Blend ingredients and serve by the teaspoonfuls into cups of boiling water.
Store in airtight container.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place a layer of graham crackers in the bottom of a cookie sheet.
Beat the egg.
Add butter, sugar and milk.
Heat until thick.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Cool.
Pour this mixture over the layer of graham crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Cut into squares and add icing.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Mix in sugar and melted margarine. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar and margarine mixture, alternately with milk. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake in a 375° oven about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 14 to 16 small muffins.

title: terrific taco biscuit pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Arrange 7 biscuits around sides and 3 on bottom of ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Press biscuits to form crust (biscuits will form petal-like shape around rim of pan).

title: potato casserole
directions: Add cheese, sour cream and salts.
Beat; add chives.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar in bowl; mix well.
Press into baking pan (9 x 12-inch) and bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon over pretzel layer.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in strawberries.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Chill until gelatin is set.

title: lemon pie(yields 1 pie)
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan with butter, lemon rind, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Stir in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fold in sour cream.
Place in baked shell.
Use egg whites, 1/4 cup sugar and cream of tartar.
Make meringue and ice pie.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Chill 2 hours.

title: company cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots. Add pineapple and marshmallows, then commercial salad dressing with leftover pineapple juice and toss cole slaw.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together the coconut and nuts.
Put in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour over coconut and pecan mixture.

title: *custard pita(pita di lapti)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cooked noodles in pan covering bottom of pan.
Beat eggs and add balance of ingredients. Slowly pour into pan over noodles which should not float.
Place in preheated 400° oven. Bake 1 hour.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Combine first four (4) ingredients. Add eggs and pecans to first mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: In casserole dish, layer beans, onions, bacon, beans, onions....etc.
Add sugar and vinegar to bacon drippings until dissolved.
Pour over layered green beans and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, mix beef broth with cornstarch and teriyaki sauce.
In a large skillet or wok, heat 1 tablespoon oil over high heat; add asparagus, pepper and onions; stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Remove to bowl.
Add remaining oil and beef; stir-fry until cooked.
Add beef broth mixture and cook, stirring constantly until thickened; add vegetables and toss.
Serve in warm pastry shells.

title: pineapple-coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl on medium speed for about 2 minutes.
Bake in tube pan (one with lift out bottom is best) for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water to a boil; add salt and macaroni.
Cook for 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; add margarine, cheese and pepper.
Stir to melt cheese.
Remove from heat and serve immediately.

title: quick chili
directions: Melt shortening in heavy skillet.
Add onions and cook until brown.
Add ground beef and brown.
Stir frequently so there will be no lumps of meat.
Add green pepper, tomato soup, salt, chili powder, black pepper, red pepper and kidney beans.
Heat mixture thoroughly and serve piping hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cornmeal griddle cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, oil and egg yolks. Blend well.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Heat chilies, tomatoes and onion.
Add cheese.
Cook 1 minute on high.
Stir and continue cooking for 7 to 8 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: hamburger and potato hot dish
directions: In a casserole or small roaster, place hamburger.
Add potatoes and soups.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour until potatoes are done.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flavoring in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, 25 to 30 minutes, stirring often.
Add salt, if needed.
Add flavoring and dried fruit, if desired.
Serve hot or cold.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine the sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add fruit.
Mix well and let stand 20 minutes.
Spoon into (9-inch) pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Put on top crust.
Moisten edge of crust to form seal. Bake at 400° about 45 minutes.

title: apple-carrot-pineapple dessert
directions: Make the jello to box directions.
(Pineapple juice can be used along with water.)
Let jello cool until it starts to thicken, then add the rest of the ingredients and chill in refrigerator.

title: nonfat yogurt muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray 6 large or 12 regular size muffin tins with baking spray.
Fill batter 3/4 way up.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: no fail pecan pie
directions: Cream together sugar, syrup, and butter.
Ad eggs one at a time and beat well.
Fold in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50-55 minutes or until center is firm.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers & onions. Cover with salt & ice. Let stand 3 hours. Drain & put in gallon jar. Dissolve sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric & alum. Pour over cucumbers & onion & put in refrigerator. They are ready to eat in 7-10 days. Can be kept in refrigerator for a long time. I have had them for a year.

title: barbecue beef(30 buns)
directions: Dump into big roaster pan.
Cover.
Bake 6 hours at 300°. After 3 hours, take forks and shred.
Remove fat and bones.
Every hour or so, do this until all is removed.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Basting a turkey all night is "for the birds!"
Rub thawed turkey with melted butter.
Stuff it with onion, celery and potato; salt and pepper bird.
Place in covered container.
Add 5 to 6 cups hot water.
Cover pan with foil, then put lid on.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Place pan in oven and bake at 500° for 1 hour, then turn oven off and leave overnight (don't open oven door!).

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt bars with marshmallows.
Add milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust; let set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: veal saute with dutchess potatoes
directions: Mix flour, 2 teaspoons salt, the paprika and pepper.
Coat veal with mixture.
Cook veal in hot oil in 12-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Add wine, water, onions, carrots and rosemary.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until veal and vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together the eggs, oil, sugar and zucchini. Add vanilla. Gradually add flour, soda, cinnamon, raisins and nuts. Put into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except lettuce. Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: sausage bread
directions: Allow dough to rise until nearly doubled.
Meanwhile in a skillet over medium heat, cook and crumble sausage.
Add garlic powder and chopped onion.
Cool.
Roll bread dough into a 16 x 12-inch rectangle pan.
Spread the sausage mixture over dough to within 1-inch of edge.
Spread Mozzarella cheese on top of sausage mixture.
Use as much cheese as you desire.
Roll jelly style and seal edges of roll with your hands.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then lemonade concentrate and food coloring if desired.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead well and cover dough. Every hour, for 5 hours, knead the dough down again.
Then shape the dough into hamburger buns or rolls.
After they rise (I wait until morning), bake at 325° for 15 minutes or light golden brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Drain chicken well and flake into bowl.
Add onion, eggs, green pepper and pickles (to individual taste).
Add enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Taste and salt if needed.
Chill overnight to allow flavors to marry.
Just before serving, add almonds and mix well.
Do not add almonds sooner, as they will soften.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix and blend together well first 4 ingredients.
Add chopped onion.
Spread mixture on flour tortillas and roll up.
Chill for 1 hour.
Slice into round sections and serve.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Pour in tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Put oil and melted butter in 13 x 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Shake chicken pieces in bag containing flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Place chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°. Turn chicken skin side up.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Spoon lemon sauce over chicken pieces and return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown hamburger meat and sausage; drain.
Melt in Velveeta over low heat.
Add dash of garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce. Spoon onto bread.
Bake for a few minutes at 250° to melt onto bread.
Serve hot, or can be frozen to bake at a later time.

title: tom's white chili
directions: In small frypan over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook onion, garlic and cumin until onion is tender.
Put all ingredients into a crock-pot (except cheese and Tabasco sauce). Simmer overnight or make in the morning and cook while you're at work!
Make sure chicken is cooked thoroughly, at least 4 to 5 hours on high simmer.
Add hot pepper sauce to taste and garnish with shredded cheese.
Great with corn bread and a real hit at Superbowl parties! Makes approximately 8 main dish servings. Lo-Cal too!

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add orange juice. Refrigerate until partly congealed.
Add mandarin oranges (drained) and crushed pineapple (drained).
Chill until firm. Mix lemon instant pudding pie filling to directions on box and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over Jell-O mixture.

title: savory baked spaghetti
directions: Cook onions and garlic in bacon grease or oil in skillet for 5 minutes.
Add chuck; cook, stirring occasionally, until meat loses its red color.
Stir in salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Discard garlic.
Add chili powder and water.
Break half of the uncooked spaghetti into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour on half of sauce; sprinkle with half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 325°. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Mix Crisco into flour mixture with blender or a fork until the mixture looks like coarse cornmeal.
Stir in grated cheese.
Add milk to Crisco-flour mixture.
Mix enough to hold dough together.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit kabobs in honey mustard
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the vinegar, honey, poppy seed and mustard.
Cut any large slices of plum or nectarine.
Add plum, nectarine, strawberries and grapes to the vinegar mixture. Toss until coated.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour. Stir occasionally.
Drain fruit; keep marinade.
Put fruit onto skewers (can use bamboo).
Brush with marinade before serving.

title: easy chocolate fondue
directions: *Suggested fondue dippers: Angel food or pound cake squares; banana, apple or pineapple chunks, strawberries, seedless grapes or marshmallows.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
May serve in a hollowed out loaf of French bread or a round loaf of sourdough bread, using cut out bread pieces for dipping.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and continue beating.
Add flour alternately with extracts and 7-Up. Pour in a large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done at 325°.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Bring water to a boil in a saucepan. Remove from heat. Add corn meal and salt.
Mix briskly with a spoon until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Mixture should be thick enough to hold its shape when dropped from spoon.
Heat skillet with oil until hot. Spoon a big tablespoonful of corn meal mixture into hot skillet and cook for about 6 to 8 minutes, turning once until bread is brown and crispy.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook rice and drain; mix all remaining ingredients together.
Bake in casserole pan at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Shred favorite cheese and sprinkle on top. Serve hot.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump the pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Dump the cherry pie filling over the pineapple and spread evenly. Sprinkle the cake mix over the cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle the nuts over the cake mix.
Cut the butter in slices and place over the cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream is nice!

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Drain rhubarb after you barely heat it.
Add butter.
Stir sugar, flour and eggs together.
Pour over rhubarb that you have placed in an uncooked crust.
Bake slow.
Don't forget to sprinkle some flour on crust before you put rhubarb in the crust.
Bake at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Mix in egg white, apple juice concentrate and melted butter.
Add flour and baking soda; mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Wear plastic gloves to work with this mixture.

title: "yummy good" cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine ingredients.
Mix together well. Pour into graham cracker crust and top with a few crumbs.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Line a well-greased cookie sheet with soda crackers.
Boil oleo and brown sugar for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes at 350°.
Immediately put chocolate bits on top.
When melted, spread out.
When cooled, remove from cookie sheet.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Combine eggs, half and half and salt in mixing bowl and mix well. Stir in enough flour to form a stiff dough. Knead on floured surface for 10 minutes. Pinch off marble-sized portions and roll each portion thin. Deep-fry in 375° oil until golden brown. Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with sugar.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate. Bake until golden brown and a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: play dough
directions: Combine and stir until smooth. Cook on top of stove 3 minutes. Stir constantly. Take off burner and let sit. It will look like you messed up, but after it sits 20 minutes or so, mix it up (with hands). It's the best play dough I've ever come across.

title: broken ice glass cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups boiling water per package of flavored gelatin. Pour each mixture in separate pie pans.
Chill until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Heat soup and milk.
Pour over rice.
Arrange chicken over this and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: caramel dip
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth.
Serve dip with sliced apples.

title: apple tart(easy)
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla and sugar together.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Add sliced apples and walnuts.
Bake at 350° in shallow greased pan (9 x 13-inch) for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: buttermilk pancake batter
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl. Whisk until blended. In a medium bowl, combine buttermilk, milk, eggs and melted butter. Whisk until blended. When your griddle pan is hot and ready to cook pancakes, add buttermilk mixture to the dry ingredients. Mix vigorously with a wooden spoon just until blended. Don't overmix the batter; a few flour lumps are okay.

title: delicious cheese cake
directions: Line spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add sour cream, then fold in beaten whites of eggs.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Leave in open oven 1 hour.
Leave in open oven 1/2 hour.

title: greek fried meatballs(keftethes)
directions: Brown onion in a little butter.
Place onions in a mixing bowl and add meat, bread crumbs, eggs, and seasonings.
Blend well and shape into size desired.
Roll lightly in flour and fry in very hot oil or butter.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Simmer in pan just before serving dinner.
Excellent for turkey dressing.

title: "philly" 15 minute cheesecake
directions: Combine together and press into the bottom of a spring-form pan.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine cabbage and smoked sausage.
Cover with water.
Cook until cabbage is cooked, stirring occasionally.
Drain 3/4 of the water off.
Add soups and milk; stir.
Heat only until hot.
Makes about 12 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: shredded yams
directions: Shred yams
into
gallon
of
water
with
salt
added. Combine sugar,
syrup
and	water in a heavy saucepan and cook until a light syrup forms.	Drain potatoes, rinse and pat dry. Place in a	12
x 6 x 3-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour pineapple juice over potatoes, then the cooked syrup.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at
about	40 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are translucent.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spray a 9 x 13 in. baking dish. Pour in and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until done.

title: golden fizz drink
directions: Mix apple juice, orange juice concentrate and carbonated water.
Pour over crushed ice and top with lemon slice.

title: avocado stuffed with pimientos
directions: Drain the pimientos and pat dry, then chop fine.
Place them in a bowl with the onion.
Combine the oil, vinegar, pepper, lemon juice and salt.
Pour over the pimientos and onion.
Marinate for about 1/2 hour.
Cut the avocados in half and remove the seeds. Place each half on a crisp lettuce leaf on a flat salad plate. Spoon the pimiento mixture evenly into the avocado halves.
Do not peel the avocado!
To eat, scoop the avocado pulp toward the center with the fork and mix with the pimiento stuffing.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in microwave.
Then mix all ingredients, except coconut and pecans, in mixing bowl.
Mix well. Then fold in coconut and pecans.
Pour into pecan shells.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: spanakopeta (spinach pie)
directions: Chop spinach, cook
briefly
to reduce bulk.
Cool; add to eggs, spices
and
cheese.	Undo the package of filo, cover pastry with towel.
Place	1
sheet
at
a time in 9 x 13-inch jelly roll pan
(butter).
Do	10
to	12
sheets, then spread spinach mixture on	them. Sprinkle with olive oil.	Cover with remaining sheets, buttering
each
one.
Cut	on the diagonal, then vertically.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: burritos
directions: Mix together the cream of mushroom soup and sour cream; put in bottom of roaster.
Fry hamburger; mix taco seasoning
and refried beans with meat.
Put mixture on top of first layer.
Put soft tacos on top of that layer.
Bake for 1 hour, then add cheese. When ready to serve, add lettuce and tomatoes.

title: christmas eggnog(makes 25 cups)
directions: Beat separately 6 egg yolks and whites.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to yolks while beating.
Beat whites stiff and then add 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix yolks and whites carefully.
Stir in heavy cream and milk.
Mix in vanilla.
Add whiskey, rum and brandy.
Stir thoroughly.
Serve very cold with grated nutmeg.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground meat and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Add barbecue sauce (and brown sugar and Ranch Style beans, if desired).
Press biscuits into a muffin tin, forming a cup.
Fill with meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring and cocoa.
Let stand.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then coloring and cocoa mixture.
Beat well.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: In a covered Dutch oven or saucepan, simmer beef in water for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Drain cooking liquid, reserving 3/4 cup.
Cool beef; shred and return to Dutch oven.
Add cabbage, barbecue sauce, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish, mustard and the reserved cooking liquid.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve warm in buns.
Serves 10.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Combine ham bone, beef bone, bacon, potatoes, onions and water in stock pot.
Cook until vegetables are almost tender.
Add undrained beans, pepperoni and saffron.
Stir in salt to taste. Simmer for 45 minutes or to desired consistency, adding additional water as needed.
Remove bones.
Cut off meat and return to soup. Heat to serving temperature.
Ladle into soup bowls.

title: rumaki
directions: Drain water chestnuts.
Mix soy sauce, brown sugar and water. Put water chestnuts in marinade and let set at least 6 hours in refrigerator.

title: crispy rice krispie cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda and salt. Blend butter and sugar thoroughly. Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Stir in dry ingredients and mix in Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° about 13 minutes.

title: easy crispy chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, combine apricot preserves, mustard and curry powder.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until preserves are melted.
Dip chicken in apricot mixture, then roll in cashews.
Place chicken in a greased 15 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Bring remaining sauce to a boil.
Serve sauce with chicken.

title: easy strawberry salad
directions: Put pineapple in a small saucepan and cook 2 minutes.
Add jello and cook 2 more minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Then add to cooled gelatin and pineapple mixture.
Chill.

title: stove top meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, crackers, onions, eggs, salt, pepper and 1/3 can tomato soup together.
Make big patties.
Cook in shortening on medium heat until brown on bottom.
Turn and reduce heat to low for approximately 30 minutes.
Add water and mustard to soup until can is full.
Stir well.
Once meat is brown all the way through, add soup mixture and baste.
Place cheese slices on top of patties and baste until cheese is melted.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt
marshmallows
in	milk,
stirring constantly. Mix with rest of ingredients.
Pack in a buttered loaf dish.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Add remaining ingredients to Bisquick mixture; make into balls.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown.

title: mexicali meat loaves
directions: Combine meat, egg, 1/4 cup tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons of green chilies, 1 tablespoon minced onion, chili powder and salt; mix well.
Shape to form 4 x 2-inch loaves.
Place in 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and drop on greased sheet and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Rinse pea pods.
Mix pea pods, soup, milk, chicken, onions, celery and chestnuts in a 3-quart saucepan.
Boil and continue stirring.
Keep warm.
Mix Bisquick, water and soy sauce until dough-like (20 vigorous strokes).
Roll dough and cut into squares. Pour mixture into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with squares and spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake approximately 15 minutes at 425° (or until golden brown).

title: apple butter
directions: Mix
all ingredients in large cooker.
Cook 30 minutes. Pour into hot jars and seal.
Really good and easy.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In Dutch oven brown beef and onion.
Add all other ingredients except parsley; bring to boil and simmer, covered, 1 hour.
May garnish with parsley.
This freezes well.

title: festive sweet potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch pan.

title: cheesy wiener wheel
directions: Spread a small amount of tomato paste on cracker.
Cut slice of cheese into 1/4's.
Place cheese on cracker.
Cut wiener in slices and place on cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese melts. Great for kids snacks!

title: tamale cheese dip
directions: Saute yellow onion in butter first.
Then combine remaining ingredients to the pan; mix and melt all ingredients together and serve in a crock-pot.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
Peel and cut into medium size pieces.
Brown onion and green pepper in butter.
Add soup.
Simmer several minutes.
Stir mixture into prepared potatoes and bake at 350° until bubbly on top.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Drain cooked broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo, eggs and onion to broccoli in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt oleo and add stuffing.
Pour on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: chicken and coke
directions: Spray crock-pot with Pam.
Skin and wash chicken.
In crock-pot, put chicken, Coke, ketchup and chopped onion.
Cook 6 hours on low.
Serve over rice.
(Pick bones out before serving.) Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: giant chewy peanut butter and apple cookies
directions: Beat peanut butter and margarine with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Add sugar and half of flour, egg whites, milk and baking soda.
Beat well.
Stir in remaining flour; add oats and apple.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet; flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes until brown.
Remove, cool on wire rack.
Store in moistproof container.
Can freeze up to 6 months.
Makes 16 to 18 cookies.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add olives and stir in taco seasoning and water.
Cover and let simmer for several minutes. Line a Pyrex pie plate or oblong dish with crescent dinner rolls. Top with crumbled corn chips.
Add hamburger mixture and top with sour cream.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Top with more corn chips.
Bake in 375° oven for approximately 25 minutes.

title: margarita fajitas
directions: Slice partially frozen round steak into thin, long strips. Marinate 2 hours in flat dish with mixture of tequila and lime juice.
After draining tequila and lime marinade, mix cooking oil, liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, salt and paprika and marinate meat, covered, for four days.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and let cool.
Put about 1/3 of the cake in bottom of bowl.
Begin to layer each remaining ingredient, using 1/3 of each item.
This includes the cake.
When you finish using all the ingredients the first time, begin another layer until you use all ingredients.
Top off with the coconut.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Melt margarine and saute celery and onion; blend with stuffing mix and broth.
Set aside.
Mix chicken, mayonnaise, salt and pepper (just a touch).
Layer half of stuffing mix in an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Top with all of chicken mix and then the remaining stuffing mix.
Mix eggs with milk and pour evenly over the chicken mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
One-half hour before baking, spread mushroom soup over casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: kathy's cranberry barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; process until smooth. This sauce is excellent on any barbecue meats and poultry.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Cube and brown the bacon and pour off the grease.
Beat together eggs, vinegar and water.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt separately.
Add bacon and liquid ingredients to saucepan on medium heat.
Add dry ingredients, stirring constantly with whip until hot and thickened.
Use over lettuce, endive or tossed salad.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Layer in a 9x13 pan all ingredients in the above order.
Bake 325° for 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, garlic powder and pepper together with a wire whisk until creamy.
Gradually add the milk and beat until smooth.
Refrigerate in a covered bowl for several hours. Dressing keeps well but may thicken as it stands.
To thin, add a little milk.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: beef roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Place in a baking pan.
Pour mushroom soup, dry onion soup mix and water over roast.
Cover and bake at 300° until done.
(May add potatoes and carrots.)

title: pat's favorite spanish rice
directions: Brown onion and rice in oil in a large skillet. Add tomato, green chilies, seasoning and stock. Cover and simmer until rice is fluffy and moist.
Make 6 to 8 servings.
